WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.337
(Channel 15ya X Google Gemini)

00:00:04.104 --> 00:00:06.673
(Round 1, starring KARINA)

00:00:07.441 --> 00:00:10.010
(&lt;I'm KARINA In Real Life, But In
An Alternate World, I'm 21-Year-Old Ji Min?&gt;)

00:00:10.477 --> 00:00:13.313
(&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;)

00:00:13.313 --> 00:00:16.650
(Who made each one, and how?)

00:00:17.518 --> 00:00:19.753
(And who won?)

00:00:20.320 --> 00:00:23.123
(The results of Round 1
will be revealed shortly)

00:00:23.123 --> 00:00:25.792
(Nah Yung Suk vs. Junior Producer
with Google Gemini)

00:00:28.595 --> 00:00:30.163
(June 8, 2026 (Mon),
eggiscoming headquarters)

00:00:30.163 --> 00:00:31.465
Please pull it.

00:00:31.865 --> 00:00:33.934
(The day the first mission theme was revealed)

00:00:34.735 --> 00:00:36.770
(The scroll reveal)

00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:38.739
Please pull it.

00:00:41.808 --> 00:00:44.044
(Round 1 topic KARINA)

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:45.812
Wow...

00:00:50.350 --> 00:00:52.185
(They met during &lt;Chattering with Nah&gt;)
Isn't she someone we met recently?

00:00:52.185 --> 00:00:53.253
(Standing up)

00:00:53.253 --> 00:00:54.588
(Repeating himself in a panic)
We met her recently, didn't we?

00:00:54.588 --> 00:00:55.889
She has time?

00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:56.990
She made time for this.

00:00:56.990 --> 00:00:58.292
Oh...

00:00:58.292 --> 00:01:00.360
(For this competition?)
Oh, she really didn't have to.

00:01:00.360 --> 00:01:02.029
She must be busy with &lt;LEMONADE&gt; right now.

00:01:02.029 --> 00:01:03.263
(Domestic promotions ended)
Promotions are over.

00:01:03.263 --> 00:01:04.431
&lt;LEMONADE&gt; is over?

00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:06.633
Really?

00:01:06.633 --> 00:01:08.402
(Shoot set for the one day her schedule is free)
She does have overseas schedules,

00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:09.736
but she gave us exactly one day.

00:01:11.038 --> 00:01:12.272
(Pressure)
Ah, why go that far...

00:01:12.272 --> 00:01:14.074
(More pressure)
Haha...

00:01:14.074 --> 00:01:15.142
Why would she?

00:01:15.142 --> 00:01:18.612
(KARINA made time for this competition)
She only had next Tuesday afternoon free for us.

00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:22.149
(Q. How did you feel when you saw the topic?)

00:01:22.149 --> 00:01:25.085
It was so different from what I expected,

00:01:25.085 --> 00:01:27.154
so I was very surprised.

00:01:27.154 --> 00:01:28.922
I honestly expected

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:31.458
someone who'd been on

00:01:31.458 --> 00:01:33.694
an eggiscoming show.

00:01:33.694 --> 00:01:35.629
But then, just as I said

00:01:35.629 --> 00:01:37.497
I wanted to work with someone lively,

00:01:37.497 --> 00:01:39.499
she's someone with so much charm,

00:01:39.499 --> 00:01:41.735
so I'm excited and curious.

00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.072
Then the shoot time

00:01:45.072 --> 00:01:46.840
and logistics are really important.

00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:48.842
From what time to what time can KARINA...

00:01:48.842 --> 00:01:51.979
From 11 AM to about 5 PM.

00:01:51.979 --> 00:01:53.680
(Total filming time, six hours)

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:56.583
Then you can take 11 to 12.

00:01:56.583 --> 00:01:59.152
Why only until 12 PM?

00:01:59.152 --> 00:02:00.420
(Joking)
And you can take the remaining two hours too.

00:02:00.420 --> 00:02:02.222
You'd get KARINA twice.

00:02:02.222 --> 00:02:03.256
Oh?

00:02:03.256 --> 00:02:04.658
We could do it like that, right?

00:02:04.658 --> 00:02:05.759
Uh, no.

00:02:05.759 --> 00:02:06.727
(Firm)

00:02:06.727 --> 00:02:07.894
(Haha)

00:02:07.894 --> 00:02:09.796
She's quick.

00:02:09.796 --> 00:02:11.365
(Q. What is your mindset going into the battle?)

00:02:11.365 --> 00:02:12.699
My mindset?

00:02:12.699 --> 00:02:14.501
Today, when Hyun Yong heard

00:02:14.501 --> 00:02:16.570
I was going on this,

00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:17.938
he told me...

00:02:17.938 --> 00:02:18.972
to crush you.

00:02:20.807 --> 00:02:22.676
(The junior producer's bold provocation)

00:02:22.676 --> 00:02:24.044
"Hey, just wipe the floor with him."

00:02:24.044 --> 00:02:25.312
- Oh...
- That's what he said.

00:02:26.113 --> 00:02:28.882
So I'll try entering with that mindset.

00:02:30.250 --> 00:02:32.052
As her senior of over 20 years,

00:02:32.052 --> 00:02:35.355
do you have any advice for your junior?

00:02:35.355 --> 00:02:36.390
That's right.

00:02:37.858 --> 00:02:39.926
(Producer Nah's advice to the junior producer)
Actually...

00:02:39.926 --> 00:02:42.229
this isn't about competing.

00:02:42.229 --> 00:02:45.365
What I want to see through this is

00:02:45.365 --> 00:02:47.234
how Gemini is used in planning

00:02:47.234 --> 00:02:49.636
by young Ji In.

00:02:49.636 --> 00:02:51.672
That's one thing, and second,

00:02:51.672 --> 00:02:52.706
after all, Ji In is

00:02:52.706 --> 00:02:54.408
the future of our company, right?

00:02:54.408 --> 00:02:56.610
This young producer...

00:02:56.610 --> 00:02:59.413
working with a popular cast member,

00:02:59.413 --> 00:03:00.881
what kind of synergy she can build.

00:03:00.881 --> 00:03:03.183
(This is why Producer Nah accepted the battle)
That's what I'm curious to see.

00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:05.919
I really want you to try

00:03:05.919 --> 00:03:07.421
everything you want, without holding back.

00:03:07.421 --> 00:03:08.855
Because this kind of opportunity...

00:03:08.855 --> 00:03:10.624
Getting to cast a great guest like that

00:03:10.624 --> 00:03:12.192
doesn't happen every day

00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:13.226
when you work as a producer.

00:03:13.226 --> 00:03:15.529
(A chance to film with a great guest)
She's so easygoing and so beautiful.

00:03:15.529 --> 00:03:17.064
She's such a great guest, so...

00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:20.200
let's have a good match.

00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:21.468
(Bow)

00:03:23.470 --> 00:03:25.972
(And so the two producers' first battle began)

00:03:26.506 --> 00:03:28.542
It's not a matter of who wins or loses.

00:03:28.542 --> 00:03:30.243
In the end, with AI's help,

00:03:30.243 --> 00:03:34.648
humanity creating higher-quality work is,

00:03:34.648 --> 00:03:37.217
I believe, a 100 percent certain future.

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:39.786
What happens

00:03:39.786 --> 00:03:42.289
when the youngest talent in our company

00:03:42.289 --> 00:03:45.292
works with the latest technology

00:03:45.292 --> 00:03:46.960
matters to me far more than winning or losing.

00:03:46.960 --> 00:03:49.129
That's what I'm most curious about.

00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:51.298
(Q. You're competing against Producer Nah)

00:03:51.298 --> 00:03:54.267
As far as I know,

00:03:54.267 --> 00:03:57.204
Yung Suk joined KBS in 2001,

00:03:57.204 --> 00:03:59.106
and I was born in 2001.

00:04:01.475 --> 00:04:06.546
The fact that I'm competing
against someone who's been a producer

00:04:06.546 --> 00:04:08.181
for my entire life

00:04:08.181 --> 00:04:12.552
makes me grateful and excited,

00:04:12.552 --> 00:04:15.689
but I still want to try winning.

00:04:15.689 --> 00:04:17.257
I'll do my best.

00:04:21.194 --> 00:04:23.563
(They have just two days to plan)

00:04:24.297 --> 00:04:26.733
(The two producers dive into planning)

00:04:28.101 --> 00:04:30.604
(The junior producer stays glued
to her computer)

00:04:31.705 --> 00:04:34.508
(Producer Nah paces, unable to sit still)

00:04:35.642 --> 00:04:38.445
(From day one,
the two spent hours deep in planning)

00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:41.148
(Current time, 12:40 AM)

00:04:41.882 --> 00:04:44.317
(Producer Cheon Ji In leaves work)

00:04:45.051 --> 00:04:46.720
(Current time, 12:50 AM)

00:04:46.720 --> 00:04:48.121
Heading home.

00:04:49.055 --> 00:04:52.159
(Both finally left work late at night)

00:04:52.859 --> 00:04:55.996
(June 9 (Tue), Phone interview)

00:04:57.364 --> 00:04:59.966
(The day of the phone interview)

00:05:03.303 --> 00:05:05.038
(Q. How did you spend yesterday?)

00:05:05.038 --> 00:05:06.773
Yesterday?

00:05:07.874 --> 00:05:10.010
It was hard.

00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:11.144
Ah...

00:05:11.144 --> 00:05:13.814
I thought I knew...

00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:15.081
a fair amount

00:05:15.081 --> 00:05:17.484
about KARINA.

00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:20.587
(The junior producer had a tough day)
I was already somewhat familiar with her.

00:05:20.587 --> 00:05:22.189
But still, somehow...

00:05:22.189 --> 00:05:24.624
(Thanks to Gemini)
I found a lot of fresh information,

00:05:24.624 --> 00:05:28.628
and I spent the day racking my brain over

00:05:28.628 --> 00:05:31.097
how to make her shine more

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:33.266
and make it fun to watch.

00:05:33.266 --> 00:05:36.503
(Q. How did you use Gemini?)
Could you tell us how you used Gemini

00:05:36.503 --> 00:05:38.905
and what information you got?

00:05:38.905 --> 00:05:41.775
First, I got links

00:05:41.775 --> 00:05:45.212
to YouTube content KARINA had appeared in,

00:05:45.212 --> 00:05:47.013
(Producer Cheon Ji In's actual usage record)
and asked it to summarize

00:05:47.013 --> 00:05:50.550
KARINA's traits that appeared there.

00:05:51.184 --> 00:05:55.055
(KARINA's favorite drama)
If she likes &lt;Boys Over Flowers&gt; and such,

00:05:55.055 --> 00:05:58.925
I wondered whether she liked

00:05:58.925 --> 00:06:00.794
that early-2000s sensibility.

00:06:00.794 --> 00:06:03.330
(Research feature)
So with the deep research feature,

00:06:03.330 --> 00:06:06.600
I asked it to analyze

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:08.902
variety formats from the early 2000s too.

00:06:09.636 --> 00:06:12.372
It scraped up a lot of information.

00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:15.108
Up to now, what was widely known to the public

00:06:15.108 --> 00:06:18.712
(Driver's license)
was the fact that she'd passed the written test.

00:06:18.712 --> 00:06:21.214
That was actually the most recent information.

00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:22.983
And Setlog?

00:06:22.983 --> 00:06:24.384
(Daily record app)
She uploads Setlog,

00:06:24.384 --> 00:06:27.087
and from there, Gemini told me

00:06:27.087 --> 00:06:28.255
that she was practicing road driving.

00:06:29.823 --> 00:06:32.626
(She found new information from Gemini)

00:06:33.894 --> 00:06:36.796
(Meanwhile,
Producer Nah has also arrived at work)

00:06:37.430 --> 00:06:40.500
(Q. How did you spend yesterday?)

00:06:40.500 --> 00:06:42.502
I just watched YouTube...

00:06:42.502 --> 00:06:43.737
trying to see...

00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.773
when KARINA looks happiest on camera these days.

00:06:46.773 --> 00:06:49.976
In any case, I want the guest to have fun.

00:06:49.976 --> 00:06:52.145
For instance...

00:06:52.145 --> 00:06:55.382
if this is a one-off event-type program,

00:06:55.382 --> 00:06:57.450
I think the most important thing

00:06:57.450 --> 00:06:58.852
is for the person appearing

00:06:58.852 --> 00:07:01.488
to enjoy the shoot and leave happy.

00:07:01.488 --> 00:07:05.358
(He looked up what the guest enjoys on YouTube)
So I wanted to see what she enjoys most.

00:07:06.893 --> 00:07:09.095
(Phone interview begins)

00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:10.764
(Producer Cheon Ji In's phone interview)

00:07:10.764 --> 00:07:11.865
Should I call?

00:07:12.699 --> 00:07:14.000
(Very nervous)

00:07:14.834 --> 00:07:16.469
(KARINA)

00:07:16.469 --> 00:07:19.139
(Her first cast interview as a producer)

00:07:19.739 --> 00:07:20.473
Hello?

00:07:20.473 --> 00:07:22.442
Hello.

00:07:22.442 --> 00:07:23.810
Hello.

00:07:23.810 --> 00:07:26.579
Hello, I'm Cheon Ji In,
the junior producer from &lt;Channel 15ya&gt;.

00:07:26.579 --> 00:07:28.214
Hello.

00:07:28.214 --> 00:07:31.618
About the shoot next Tuesday,

00:07:31.618 --> 00:07:33.920
- I wanted to ask you a few things.
- Yes.

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:34.821
(With Gemini, she starts the interview
based on prepared questions)

00:07:34.821 --> 00:07:38.158
(Newly discovered information)
You said you like the drama &lt;Boys Over Flowers&gt;.

00:07:38.158 --> 00:07:39.459
Ahahaha.

00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:42.796
(Follow-up questions on what she found)
What is it about that drama that you like?

00:07:42.796 --> 00:07:46.266
(More discovered information)
I heard you like soy milk noodles in the summer.

00:07:46.266 --> 00:07:47.534
Oh, I do like it.

00:07:47.534 --> 00:07:49.836
(aespa universe)
You're Rocket Puncher, right?

00:07:50.770 --> 00:07:53.273
Punching machines and things like that...

00:07:53.273 --> 00:07:54.407
Have you ever tried one?

00:07:55.408 --> 00:07:58.278
(Also asks about an idea planned with Gemini)
At an arcade?

00:07:58.812 --> 00:07:59.813
Oh, then...

00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:01.181
May I brag about one thing?

00:08:01.181 --> 00:08:02.215
Yes.

00:08:02.215 --> 00:08:04.150
I just got my driver's license.

00:08:05.752 --> 00:08:08.822
(Thanks to the proactive guest,
she gets useful information too)

00:08:08.822 --> 00:08:10.290
All right, take care.

00:08:10.290 --> 00:08:11.791
Yes, thank you.

00:08:11.791 --> 00:08:14.561
(That wraps up the phone interview with KARINA)

00:08:15.128 --> 00:08:17.364
(Next is Producer Nah's phone interview)

00:08:18.198 --> 00:08:19.366
Hello?

00:08:19.366 --> 00:08:20.567
Hello.

00:08:20.567 --> 00:08:22.302
Oh, RINA.

00:08:22.302 --> 00:08:24.637
(Producer Nah tries to lighten the mood
with a casual greeting)

00:08:24.637 --> 00:08:25.372
Oh, thank you

00:08:25.372 --> 00:08:27.273
for agreeing to do our program.

00:08:27.273 --> 00:08:28.575
(He begins by expressing gratitude)

00:08:28.575 --> 00:08:32.412
This is something
where you don't even know what you'll do.

00:08:32.412 --> 00:08:34.047
I'm so grateful for the courage

00:08:34.047 --> 00:08:36.249
to say yes without even knowing what it is.

00:08:36.249 --> 00:08:37.684
I like taking on challenges.

00:08:37.684 --> 00:08:39.519
All right, first, "likes challenges."

00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.121
RINA's trait.

00:08:41.121 --> 00:08:43.189
(Immediately noting the guest's traits)
"I like challenges."

00:08:43.189 --> 00:08:43.857
That scares me.

00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:45.291
Hahaha.

00:08:45.825 --> 00:08:48.828
- Can you answer simply and honestly?
- Yes!

00:08:48.828 --> 00:08:50.864
(Producer Nah's phone interview begins)
First.

00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:53.033
(During the &lt;Chattering with Nah&gt; shoot)
When we met recently,

00:08:54.134 --> 00:08:55.835
you said you were getting your license, right?

00:08:55.835 --> 00:08:56.836
Oh, yes.

00:08:56.836 --> 00:08:58.204
Uh, that...

00:08:58.204 --> 00:08:59.606
Did you only pass the written test?

00:08:59.606 --> 00:09:00.306
No way.

00:09:00.306 --> 00:09:02.042
Right now...

00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:04.077
About 30, 40 minutes ago,

00:09:04.077 --> 00:09:04.878
I got my license,

00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:06.479
and now I'm on my way to pick up the card.

00:09:06.479 --> 00:09:07.280
Got it.

00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:08.815
That's it.

00:09:08.815 --> 00:09:10.817
(Very excited)
That's it. We've got it.

00:09:10.817 --> 00:09:12.452
The show is set. We're done.

00:09:13.920 --> 00:09:16.423
(He gets excited, not knowing
the junior producer already knows too)

00:09:16.423 --> 00:09:17.323
Now when you see a steering wheel,

00:09:17.323 --> 00:09:19.192
you can't wait to grab it, right?

00:09:19.192 --> 00:09:20.627
I'm itching to.

00:09:21.728 --> 00:09:23.329
Ahaha.

00:09:23.329 --> 00:09:25.665
Next, I'll ask just a few more things.

00:09:25.665 --> 00:09:27.500
(Questions begin in earnest)

00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:31.871
Our shoot is next Tuesday, right?

00:09:31.871 --> 00:09:34.340
How tired will you be
before and after the shoot?

00:09:34.340 --> 00:09:36.943
What are your schedules before and after?

00:09:36.943 --> 00:09:40.280
(Checks the guest's condition for shoot day)
Wait, I'll check now.

00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:42.382
Normally, for meals,

00:09:42.382 --> 00:09:43.950
what do you usually have for lunch and such?

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:45.585
What do you like to eat?

00:09:46.086 --> 00:09:49.255
(Checks favorite foods and usual eating habits)
You probably eat something simple, right?

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:50.523
Between &lt;Infinite Challenge&gt;
and &lt;2 Days &amp; 1 Night&gt;,

00:09:50.523 --> 00:09:52.258
which do you like more?

00:09:52.258 --> 00:09:54.694
(He also checks what kind of content she likes)
Why are you doing this?

00:09:54.694 --> 00:09:56.696
(With tears in his eyes)
As far as I know, you're a huge fan

00:09:56.696 --> 00:09:58.298
of &lt;Infinite Challenge&gt;.

00:09:58.731 --> 00:10:00.667
You mentioned the cult recruiter episode, right?

00:10:00.667 --> 00:10:01.367
Yes.

00:10:01.367 --> 00:10:03.269
Back then, you had worries

00:10:03.269 --> 00:10:05.205
and things were complicated,
so that was probably why, right?

00:10:05.205 --> 00:10:06.206
Right.

00:10:06.206 --> 00:10:08.041
What was your biggest worry then?

00:10:08.041 --> 00:10:09.876
(Producer Nah smoothly continues
the phone interview)

00:10:09.876 --> 00:10:10.710
Okay, I get it.

00:10:10.710 --> 00:10:11.744
Time's up.

00:10:11.744 --> 00:10:13.446
Huh? It's already over?

00:10:13.446 --> 00:10:14.047
Uh, RINA...

00:10:14.047 --> 00:10:16.382
I'll come up with a fun program,

00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:17.884
so let's have a good shoot.

00:10:17.884 --> 00:10:19.853
I'm looking forward to it.
I'll maintain my stamina for that day.

00:10:19.853 --> 00:10:22.455
Yes, all right. Bye.

00:10:22.455 --> 00:10:23.823
(He made full use of the ten-minute call)
Take care.

00:10:25.058 --> 00:10:27.060
Oh, well,

00:10:27.060 --> 00:10:30.697
(Smug)
I think I really hit the nail on the head.

00:10:30.697 --> 00:10:32.732
I mean, did Ji In

00:10:32.732 --> 00:10:34.300
not ask questions like this?

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.035
(Smug)
I guess Gemini didn't teach her

00:10:36.035 --> 00:10:37.337
that part.

00:10:37.337 --> 00:10:39.038
What the guest feels most stressed by,

00:10:39.038 --> 00:10:40.773
what they most want to do,

00:10:40.773 --> 00:10:42.675
and what they miss most.

00:10:42.675 --> 00:10:43.877
That's how you get a full picture

00:10:43.877 --> 00:10:46.279
of a person.

00:10:47.080 --> 00:10:48.314
What I'm thinking now

00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:49.983
is a huge project

00:10:49.983 --> 00:10:52.452
that mixes all of this.

00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:54.687
(He plans to mix all the information he got)
Mixing everything that came out.

00:10:54.687 --> 00:10:57.590
(What kind of plan will it be?)
One big framework bringing it all together.

00:10:58.758 --> 00:11:00.727
(Q. How will you prepare
for tomorrow's planning pitch?)

00:11:00.727 --> 00:11:02.295
The pitch?

00:11:02.295 --> 00:11:03.863
First, based on the plan,

00:11:03.863 --> 00:11:08.134
I'll try to make it as intuitive as possible.

00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:11.571
I'll use Gemini to create some images too,

00:11:11.571 --> 00:11:12.539
and for the PPT,

00:11:12.539 --> 00:11:15.341
I'll try using Gemini for the first draft.

00:11:17.377 --> 00:11:20.647
(After finishing the short but important
phone interviews with the guest)

00:11:22.448 --> 00:11:25.919
(The two producers continue preparing
for their planning pitches)

00:11:26.686 --> 00:11:28.821
(June 10 (Wed), Planning pitch)

00:11:28.821 --> 00:11:31.157
(The day of the planning pitch)

00:11:31.758 --> 00:11:33.726
(&lt;Channel 15ya&gt; team meeting room)

00:11:38.698 --> 00:11:39.832
What's with the applause?

00:11:39.832 --> 00:11:40.867
Oh, we're just happy to see you.

00:11:41.668 --> 00:11:45.438
(Producer Nah Yung Suk's planning pitch)
Isn't this applause a little too random?

00:11:45.838 --> 00:11:46.439
Ah...

00:11:46.439 --> 00:11:48.408
No one talks to me.

00:11:49.008 --> 00:11:50.810
(Very lonely)

00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:53.680
I really do feel lonely.

00:11:53.680 --> 00:11:56.149
I mean, planning is supposed to be

00:11:56.149 --> 00:11:58.251
producers and writers gathering

00:11:58.251 --> 00:12:00.086
happily,

00:12:00.086 --> 00:12:01.187
asking "What do you think?"

00:12:01.187 --> 00:12:03.256
That's how it's supposed to work, right?

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:07.594
(This battle mission has to be handled alone)

00:12:07.594 --> 00:12:08.294
And also,

00:12:08.294 --> 00:12:10.930
I've never given a pitch in my life.

00:12:10.930 --> 00:12:12.532
So I just need to tell you

00:12:12.532 --> 00:12:14.167
what kind of show I'm making, right?

00:12:14.634 --> 00:12:16.102
I'm really nervous.

00:12:17.303 --> 00:12:19.639
(Planning pitch begins)

00:12:19.639 --> 00:12:20.607
Let's start with the title.

00:12:22.342 --> 00:12:24.110
(Very nervous)

00:12:24.911 --> 00:12:27.947
(He begins presenting his plan to his juniors)

00:12:27.947 --> 00:12:29.882
It sounds like
one of those modern web-novel titles.

00:12:31.484 --> 00:12:33.219
This is the title I thought of.

00:12:34.454 --> 00:12:39.359
&lt;I'm KARINA In Real Life, But In
An Alternate World, I'm 21-Year-Old Ji Min ?&gt;

00:12:39.359 --> 00:12:40.393
That's the premise.

00:12:40.393 --> 00:12:42.328
(Producer Nah's program)
The reason I thought of this is this.

00:12:42.328 --> 00:12:43.863
Back when we...

00:12:43.863 --> 00:12:45.898
recorded &lt;Chattering with Nah&gt; with aespa,

00:12:45.898 --> 00:12:48.901
they talked about

00:12:48.901 --> 00:12:49.702
"feeling stuck at a certain age."

00:12:49.702 --> 00:12:51.537
"I feel like I'm stuck at 21."

00:12:51.537 --> 00:12:53.206
(That line stuck in Producer Nah's mind)
I asked why and they talked about it.

00:12:53.206 --> 00:12:55.575
Back then, ahead of debut, she was nervous,

00:12:55.575 --> 00:12:57.644
she had so many thoughts,

00:12:57.644 --> 00:12:58.945
and she was worried about
whether things would work out.

00:13:00.046 --> 00:13:03.316
Of course,
this is a variety show meant to be fun,

00:13:03.316 --> 00:13:05.018
but through this brief experience,

00:13:05.018 --> 00:13:06.586
to the time when

00:13:06.586 --> 00:13:08.087
she was anxious and the future was uncertain,

00:13:08.087 --> 00:13:09.255
an alternate world,

00:13:09.255 --> 00:13:11.724
let's send KARINA.

00:13:11.724 --> 00:13:12.692
That's the concept.

00:13:12.692 --> 00:13:16.162
(To leave KARINA with a vivid memory)
Though it'll be a brief experience.

00:13:16.162 --> 00:13:17.163
So the genre is

00:13:18.564 --> 00:13:20.667
(Role-Playing Game, RPG genre)

00:13:21.501 --> 00:13:24.170
(Inspired by KARINA saying in the phone
interview that she likes game-like content)

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:26.306
I've never played an RPG before.

00:13:26.306 --> 00:13:27.440
(Not confident)

00:13:27.440 --> 00:13:29.208
And I was like,

00:13:29.208 --> 00:13:30.109
"Is this okay?"

00:13:30.109 --> 00:13:32.478
I've never played this kind of game.

00:13:32.478 --> 00:13:33.880
So please take a look.

00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:36.182
(A very new challenge for Producer Nah too)
I don't play games like this, so I'm not sure.

00:13:36.683 --> 00:13:38.184
There's a coffee shop in Seoul.

00:13:38.184 --> 00:13:40.720
(Item explanation begins in earnest)
This is a real coffee shop we'll need to rent.

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:42.555
Who is aespa's helper?

00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:44.324
- Naevis?
- Naevis.

00:13:44.324 --> 00:13:46.726
(Combined with aespa's universe)

00:13:46.726 --> 00:13:48.861
There is an office worker
sitting alone with a laptop.

00:13:48.861 --> 00:13:50.897
(Actor needed)

00:13:50.897 --> 00:13:53.232
I'll ask a trainee to do it,

00:13:53.232 --> 00:13:56.269
(Casting an actual trainee too)
and seat her there.

00:13:56.269 --> 00:13:57.970
I want it to feel

00:13:57.970 --> 00:14:00.340
like KARINA is talking to her past self.

00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:01.841
(A heart-to-heart with the trainee)
Actually, this scene

00:14:01.841 --> 00:14:04.677
is the most important scene to me.

00:14:04.677 --> 00:14:06.913
This is a huge project.

00:14:06.913 --> 00:14:09.182
(He really combined everything
from yesterday's interview)

00:14:09.615 --> 00:14:11.050
It's a little loose.

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:15.188
(Producer Nah's planning pitch ends)
For now, that's the idea.

00:14:15.188 --> 00:14:17.357
(Q. How did it feel to give the pitch?)
Thinking through it all alone

00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:18.691
and laying that plan out

00:14:20.093 --> 00:14:22.395
made me feel a little flustered.

00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:24.664
What if people...

00:14:24.664 --> 00:14:26.632
think this isn't fun?

00:14:26.632 --> 00:14:28.034
That sense of tension I felt

00:14:28.034 --> 00:14:30.770
when I was very young

00:14:30.770 --> 00:14:32.305
came rushing back for the first time in so long,

00:14:32.305 --> 00:14:33.940
and honestly, it threw me off.

00:14:34.974 --> 00:14:36.075
(Q. The shoot is right around the corner)

00:14:36.075 --> 00:14:38.878
I'll try to have fun shooting it.

00:14:38.878 --> 00:14:41.214
It's been a while
since I've done something this different,

00:14:41.214 --> 00:14:43.282
so honestly, it's fun.

00:14:43.282 --> 00:14:45.218
So I'll try to make the shoot fun.

00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:49.155
(The meeting room gets lively)

00:14:49.155 --> 00:14:50.123
There you are.

00:14:50.123 --> 00:14:51.624
(Bow)

00:14:51.624 --> 00:14:53.593
(Producer Cheon Ji In's planning pitch)

00:14:53.593 --> 00:14:54.827
Cheon Ji In.

00:14:54.827 --> 00:14:58.398
- Cheon Ji In.
- Cheon Ji In.

00:14:59.866 --> 00:15:02.602
(The pitch begins in earnest)

00:15:02.602 --> 00:15:03.603
Hello.

00:15:06.606 --> 00:15:08.574
(Producer Cheon Ji In's program,
&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;)

00:15:08.574 --> 00:15:09.575
I used the Gemini Nano Banana.

00:15:11.444 --> 00:15:13.012
I am Cheon Ji In, presenting the plan for

00:15:13.012 --> 00:15:15.114
&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;.

00:15:18.718 --> 00:15:21.921
First, when I heard KARINA was the guest,

00:15:21.921 --> 00:15:24.390
I did some research on my own

00:15:24.390 --> 00:15:27.059
and had many conversations with Gemini.

00:15:27.059 --> 00:15:29.595
The piece of information that stood out most

00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:32.498
was KARINA's Met Gala debut.

00:15:32.498 --> 00:15:35.635
I started with the keyword "Met Gala,"

00:15:35.635 --> 00:15:39.105
and thought we could make something timely,

00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:41.140
so with summer in mind,

00:15:41.140 --> 00:15:44.710
I asked Gemini about KARINA.

00:15:44.710 --> 00:15:46.479
Then Gemini told me

00:15:46.479 --> 00:15:49.115
that "KARINA mentioned

00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:52.418
soy milk noodles as a summer delicacy."

00:15:52.418 --> 00:15:56.823
With "Met Gala" and "soy milk noodles"
as keywords,

00:15:56.823 --> 00:15:58.791
since it's the "Met Gala,"

00:15:58.791 --> 00:16:00.293
"Maetdol Gala."

00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:01.727
(Embarrassed)

00:16:01.727 --> 00:16:03.329
With a maetdol...

00:16:03.329 --> 00:16:05.798
I thought, "grind beans with a millstone."

00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:07.834
So I thought she could grind beans herself
with a millstone,

00:16:07.834 --> 00:16:11.103
and make soy milk noodles herself.

00:16:11.103 --> 00:16:13.573
That's how I came up with the idea.

00:16:13.573 --> 00:16:15.975
With "soy milk noodles" and "millstone"...

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:18.778
(Producer Cheon Ji In made
intuitive images using Gemini)

00:16:18.778 --> 00:16:20.847
(KARINA holding soy milk noodles
in front of a Met Gala red carpet)

00:16:20.847 --> 00:16:23.082
With the "dol" just barely visible...

00:16:23.082 --> 00:16:24.750
(Maetdol Gala invitation)

00:16:25.418 --> 00:16:26.886
(Inside the office) there's a long staircase.

00:16:27.887 --> 00:16:30.189
(A Maetdol Gala red carpet
inside the office building)

00:16:30.189 --> 00:16:32.992
For the rooftop setup I actually imagined,

00:16:32.992 --> 00:16:34.627
(Shoot setup image)
there'd be a wooden platform on the right,

00:16:34.627 --> 00:16:36.929
and it would look something like this.

00:16:36.929 --> 00:16:39.732
(Expected shot of KARINA grinding
with the millstone)

00:16:40.433 --> 00:16:42.768
(The junior producer used Gemini
to make an intuitive pitch)

00:16:42.768 --> 00:16:43.769
Thank you.

00:16:46.305 --> 00:16:48.674
(Producer Cheon Ji In's planning pitch ends)

00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:51.777
This time, I used Gemini to create

00:16:51.777 --> 00:16:53.379
the setup and such.

00:16:53.379 --> 00:16:56.883
So looking at those images

00:16:56.883 --> 00:16:59.352
made me rethink a few parts too.

00:16:59.352 --> 00:17:01.153
(Q. The shoot is right around the corner)

00:17:01.153 --> 00:17:02.822
After putting in this much work,

00:17:02.822 --> 00:17:04.056
I want to win.

00:17:05.658 --> 00:17:07.493
(The junior producer prepared
through sleepless nights for two days)

00:17:07.493 --> 00:17:08.828
After spending this much time...

00:17:08.828 --> 00:17:10.630
I mean...

00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:12.365
I want to win.

00:17:12.365 --> 00:17:13.499
If I may say so, just this once.

00:17:15.134 --> 00:17:17.103
(Her competitive spirit is fired up
for this battle)

00:17:17.103 --> 00:17:18.304
Thank you.

00:17:18.304 --> 00:17:19.438
Thank you.

00:17:19.438 --> 00:17:22.408
(Everything is ready for the real shoot)

00:17:23.342 --> 00:17:26.445
(How will the two producers' plans
play out on set?)

00:17:27.380 --> 00:17:29.815
(June 16 (Tue), Main shoot)

00:17:29.815 --> 00:17:32.652
(Finally, the shoot day)

00:17:33.219 --> 00:17:35.421
(Which shoot starts first?)

00:17:37.323 --> 00:17:40.960
(&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;)

00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:44.430
(Just as planned with Gemini)
If we lay out the red carpet long like this,

00:17:44.430 --> 00:17:49.302
(Cheon Ji In's imagination became reality)
with this hidden photo wall...

00:17:49.302 --> 00:17:52.305
(June 16, 2026 (Tue), 8:30 AM)

00:17:52.305 --> 00:17:53.506
Let's go.

00:17:53.973 --> 00:17:56.309
(Someone arrives to cheers)

00:17:56.309 --> 00:17:57.476
Hello.

00:17:57.476 --> 00:17:59.779
The director has arrived.

00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.447
Hello.

00:18:01.447 --> 00:18:03.683
(Producer Cheon, director of &lt;Maetdol Gala&gt;)
The director has arrived.

00:18:03.683 --> 00:18:05.885
(Runs away)

00:18:05.885 --> 00:18:07.053
(Planning image)

00:18:07.053 --> 00:18:10.489
(The set from the plan now stands before Ji In)

00:18:11.023 --> 00:18:12.491
How is it?

00:18:12.491 --> 00:18:14.193
Oh, it's so good.

00:18:14.193 --> 00:18:16.696
- Is it perfect?
- Yes.

00:18:16.696 --> 00:18:19.432
Did you get some sleep?

00:18:19.432 --> 00:18:21.267
I barely slept.

00:18:21.267 --> 00:18:21.968
I woke up at 4,

00:18:21.968 --> 00:18:22.768
then at 5,

00:18:22.768 --> 00:18:23.803
then at 6,

00:18:23.803 --> 00:18:25.471
then at 7.

00:18:25.471 --> 00:18:29.275
(Q. What worries you most today?)

00:18:29.275 --> 00:18:30.743
It's so hot,

00:18:30.743 --> 00:18:33.946
so I'm worried she'll have a hard time

00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:35.715
working the millstone.

00:18:35.715 --> 00:18:37.650
(Q. What is your mindset today?)

00:18:37.650 --> 00:18:40.119
"I am Nah Yung Suk."

00:18:40.119 --> 00:18:43.456
I'll take it on with that mindset.

00:18:43.456 --> 00:18:44.557
Thank you.

00:18:44.557 --> 00:18:46.325
You can do it.

00:18:46.325 --> 00:18:49.095
(The junior producer is brimming with spirit)

00:18:49.095 --> 00:18:50.630
- Let's get to work.
- Yes.

00:18:51.397 --> 00:18:53.165
(She first goes to find a senior producer)

00:18:53.165 --> 00:18:54.600
(Bae Ye Jin/6th year/In charge of fixed cameras)

00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:56.636
Do you want to check the fixed-camera angle?

00:18:56.636 --> 00:18:57.803
Oh, yes.

00:18:58.671 --> 00:19:01.607
(The junior producer starts checking
the setup in detail)

00:19:01.607 --> 00:19:06.779
(Full shot)
That'll catch a full after the platform reveal,

00:19:06.779 --> 00:19:10.850
(Tight shot)
so should this show the millstone and KARINA?

00:19:10.850 --> 00:19:11.717
(She adjusts camera angles
on the spot with ease)

00:19:11.717 --> 00:19:13.753
- After that reveal?
- Yes.

00:19:14.553 --> 00:19:16.088
(Back full shot)
There's a rear wide camera here too.

00:19:16.088 --> 00:19:18.424
Oh, this is a full back view.

00:19:18.424 --> 00:19:20.960
(There are 23 fixed cameras to check)

00:19:20.960 --> 00:19:23.262
(Ji Chang Gyu/Director
/Head of the camera team)

00:19:23.262 --> 00:19:25.364
From the first floor, the follow shot

00:19:25.364 --> 00:19:27.266
will be done by that director filming now.

00:19:27.867 --> 00:19:30.536
(Camera team movements are checked too)

00:19:31.137 --> 00:19:32.505
(Next, she meets...)

00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:33.639
Thanks in advance.

00:19:33.639 --> 00:19:35.374
You...

00:19:35.975 --> 00:19:37.643
(Jeong Jeong Heon/5th year/Bodyguard role)

00:19:37.643 --> 00:19:42.682
On the first floor,
KARINA will give you her ticket.

00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:46.018
Then check the ticket in front of the elevator

00:19:46.018 --> 00:19:48.087
and say, "You may enter."

00:19:48.087 --> 00:19:50.089
(She explains today's role in detail)
Then get into the elevator with her.

00:19:50.723 --> 00:19:52.191
Hello.

00:19:53.592 --> 00:19:55.628
(Moon Da Som/Writer/Today's host)
So anyway...

00:19:55.628 --> 00:19:58.297
(They coordinate the Maet Chance segment)
At first, say there's a human millstone chance.

00:19:58.297 --> 00:19:59.098
Just that much.

00:19:59.098 --> 00:20:00.933
"If you clear the Maet Quiz now,"

00:20:00.933 --> 00:20:02.935
"you can use the human millstone."

00:20:02.935 --> 00:20:04.370
And make (the quiz question) easy.

00:20:04.370 --> 00:20:06.005
The Maet-ter is,

00:20:06.005 --> 00:20:07.139
how old is KARINA?

00:20:07.840 --> 00:20:09.675
(Reality check)

00:20:09.675 --> 00:20:12.178
Is this okay?

00:20:12.178 --> 00:20:13.779
Producer, is this the right tone?

00:20:13.779 --> 00:20:14.880
- Yes.
- Oh, it is?

00:20:14.880 --> 00:20:16.015
(Firm)

00:20:16.015 --> 00:20:17.416
Okay, do it again. The Maet-ter is...

00:20:17.416 --> 00:20:19.785
How old is KARINA?

00:20:19.785 --> 00:20:21.220
(The director is satisfied)

00:20:23.756 --> 00:20:25.758
(Meanwhile, the set springs into action
at the sound of someone coming up)

00:20:26.726 --> 00:20:28.327
(Polite)
Hello.

00:20:28.794 --> 00:20:31.897
(Who has everyone on edge?)

00:20:31.897 --> 00:20:34.667
Oh, you laid a red carpet on the stairs?

00:20:34.667 --> 00:20:36.736
(Rhee Myung Han/CEO
/Role of Seasonal Produce Doctor)

00:20:36.736 --> 00:20:38.904
(The CEO gladly stepped up
at the junior producer's request)

00:20:38.904 --> 00:20:41.507
Ji In will probably explain today's shoot.

00:20:41.507 --> 00:20:42.975
(Pressure)
Sure, sure.

00:20:43.809 --> 00:20:46.779
(A junior in her third year
is putting the CEO to work)

00:20:46.779 --> 00:20:48.114
So, do you think you can win?

00:20:48.114 --> 00:20:49.381
Ah.

00:20:49.381 --> 00:20:50.082
(Boldly)
I can win.

00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:52.985
(She starts with a nervous joke)

00:20:52.985 --> 00:20:54.687
First,

00:20:54.687 --> 00:20:56.489
this is called the "Maetdol Gala."

00:20:56.489 --> 00:20:57.356
Maetdol...

00:20:57.356 --> 00:20:58.524
Gala.

00:20:59.225 --> 00:21:01.160
Do you know the Met Gala?

00:21:01.160 --> 00:21:02.928
No, I don't.

00:21:02.928 --> 00:21:05.998
That fashion magazine editor,

00:21:05.998 --> 00:21:09.268
Anna Wintour, hosts this charity event.

00:21:09.268 --> 00:21:13.305
(The junior Producer breaks it down for the CEO)
KARINA made her debut there this year.

00:21:13.305 --> 00:21:16.509
So we turned that into "Maetdol" Gala.

00:21:16.509 --> 00:21:18.244
The host of this Maetdol Gala

00:21:18.244 --> 00:21:19.812
is Seasonal Produce Doctor Rhee Myung Han.

00:21:21.747 --> 00:21:24.884
(His alter ego keeps getting busier)

00:21:25.384 --> 00:21:27.653
Oh, this is a lot of pressure.

00:21:27.653 --> 00:21:30.489
And when KARINA is working the millstone,

00:21:30.489 --> 00:21:33.359
if she gets tired, she can use a chance.

00:21:33.359 --> 00:21:35.427
Then as the Human Millstone... (you'll come out)

00:21:36.061 --> 00:21:38.364
(Rhee Myung Han/CEO
/Seasonal Produce Doctor and Human Millstone)

00:21:38.364 --> 00:21:40.032
This is pretty cult.

00:21:40.032 --> 00:21:42.067
(The host feels burdened by his many roles)

00:21:42.067 --> 00:21:43.269
Okay.

00:21:43.269 --> 00:21:45.304
(Readily agrees)

00:21:45.304 --> 00:21:47.439
Once we take a photo of the soy milk noodles

00:21:47.439 --> 00:21:50.075
and then you eat it together, that's the end.

00:21:50.075 --> 00:21:50.943
All right.

00:21:50.943 --> 00:21:52.244
Thank you.

00:21:52.244 --> 00:21:53.479
I'll see you later.

00:21:53.479 --> 00:21:55.548
(She safely cleared the biggest hurdle)

00:21:56.182 --> 00:21:59.718
(Near the end of setup,
Producer Ji In turns to Gemini)

00:21:59.718 --> 00:22:00.486
Hey, Gemini.

00:22:01.887 --> 00:22:03.956
Behind this photo wall,

00:22:03.956 --> 00:22:07.059
I've set up a platform and a millstone.

00:22:07.059 --> 00:22:08.894
When we remove the photo wall

00:22:08.894 --> 00:22:10.863
and KARINA sees this setup,
how do you think she'll react?

00:22:12.164 --> 00:22:14.466
Placing the millstone and platform
behind the photo wall

00:22:14.466 --> 00:22:16.235
is a truly fresh attempt.

00:22:16.235 --> 00:22:18.103
Modern Met Gala sensibility

00:22:18.103 --> 00:22:20.272
combines with Korean traditional elements,

00:22:20.272 --> 00:22:22.441
creating a very unique atmosphere.

00:22:22.441 --> 00:22:26.478
(Gemini's glowing review puts her more at ease)
KARINA will feel the charm of this unexpected...

00:22:26.478 --> 00:22:28.414
With the ingredients we discussed,

00:22:28.414 --> 00:22:32.017
(She also checks the ingredients)
I set up the ingredients. What do you think?

00:22:32.785 --> 00:22:35.955
Wow, the ingredients you prepared
look really good.

00:22:35.955 --> 00:22:39.225
The beans for black soy milk noodles,
sesame, and black sesame,

00:22:39.225 --> 00:22:42.094
and even tomatoes and eggs are perfect.

00:22:42.094 --> 00:22:45.965
(Thanks to that, setup was completed smoothly)
They'll be tasty and filling soy milk noodles.

00:22:47.266 --> 00:22:50.102
(Meanwhile, &lt;I'm KARINA In Real Life, But In
An Alternate World, I'm 21-Year-Old Ji Min?&gt;)

00:22:51.337 --> 00:22:55.608
(The crew has been busy since morning)

00:22:56.242 --> 00:22:57.943
(Fixed camera)

00:22:58.611 --> 00:23:00.179
(Camera)

00:23:00.880 --> 00:23:02.514
(Audio)

00:23:02.948 --> 00:23:04.783
(Even props)

00:23:05.417 --> 00:23:10.089
(The three-hour setup is almost complete)

00:23:10.489 --> 00:23:12.825
(Current time, 11 AM)

00:23:14.293 --> 00:23:15.461
Hello.

00:23:15.928 --> 00:23:17.863
Director, the office worker actor has arrived.

00:23:18.330 --> 00:23:20.466
(The actors have also arrived on set)

00:23:20.866 --> 00:23:22.368
So this is kind of, then...

00:23:22.368 --> 00:23:23.469
like a mockumentary?

00:23:23.469 --> 00:23:24.603
I think so.

00:23:24.603 --> 00:23:26.005
Ah, this is so hard for me...

00:23:26.005 --> 00:23:28.507
(While the actors introduce themselves)
I don't know what I'm supposed to do.

00:23:29.041 --> 00:23:31.877
(Producer Nah has also arrived at the cafe)

00:23:31.877 --> 00:23:33.679
Why are you already filming?

00:23:33.679 --> 00:23:35.114
It's behind-the-scenes.

00:23:37.149 --> 00:23:38.450
That makes me nervous.

00:23:38.450 --> 00:23:40.853
(His tense, hunched back)

00:23:40.853 --> 00:23:42.087
Well...

00:23:42.087 --> 00:23:43.789
Please introduce the actors one by one.

00:23:43.789 --> 00:23:45.925
(Producer Nah checks in with the actors first)

00:23:45.925 --> 00:23:48.727
I thought we could meet briefly and talk.

00:23:48.727 --> 00:23:50.262
Please come this way.

00:23:50.262 --> 00:23:51.964
Where are our positions?

00:23:51.964 --> 00:23:53.599
Where is the owner at the very beginning?

00:23:53.599 --> 00:23:55.634
(Koo Hee Ryeong/Actor/Cult recruiter,
Yoo Hyeon Jong/Actor/Cafe owner)

00:23:55.634 --> 00:23:57.770
(Moon Dong Ho/Actor/Couple (male))

00:23:57.770 --> 00:23:59.371
(Gong Su Ho/Actor/Couple (female))

00:23:59.371 --> 00:24:01.140
(Ji Woong Bae/Actor/Office worker)

00:24:01.140 --> 00:24:02.975
(Camera director)
Jeong Pyo, can you come here?

00:24:02.975 --> 00:24:03.976
Yes.

00:24:03.976 --> 00:24:05.878
This is just to explain things...

00:24:05.878 --> 00:24:07.279
and check everyone's positions.

00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:10.182
(For now, he tries to keep it simple)
It would be best if you sit and listen.

00:24:10.182 --> 00:24:14.453
You've probably heard
a rough explanation about today.

00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:16.455
We're filming a variety show
with KARINA as the lead,

00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:17.890
a short-form variety show,

00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:19.291
something along those lines.

00:24:19.291 --> 00:24:20.759
The title is...

00:24:20.759 --> 00:24:21.994
Alternate...

00:24:21.994 --> 00:24:23.629
Wait, what was the title again?

00:24:24.129 --> 00:24:25.364
&lt;I'm KARINA In Real Life, But In
An Alternate World, I'm 21-Year-Old Ji Min?&gt;

00:24:25.364 --> 00:24:26.799
"I'm KARINA In Real Life..."

00:24:26.799 --> 00:24:29.068
(He must be nervous
He even forgot the title)

00:24:29.068 --> 00:24:30.869
(Starts again)
Anyway, this...

00:24:30.869 --> 00:24:34.239
may not follow the script.

00:24:34.239 --> 00:24:37.376
Because KARINA really doesn't know anything

00:24:37.376 --> 00:24:38.744
and is just coming.

00:24:38.744 --> 00:24:41.981
(There are instructions for the alternate world)
She thinks she's just here to buy coffee, but...

00:24:41.981 --> 00:24:43.515
"You're the part-timer."

00:24:43.515 --> 00:24:44.817
"You have to work here."

00:24:44.817 --> 00:24:46.352
When you say things like that,
KARINA will be...

00:24:46.352 --> 00:24:47.886
"Uh, no, that's not it."

00:24:47.886 --> 00:24:49.688
"I just came to buy coffee..."

00:24:49.688 --> 00:24:52.725
(He naturally connects it to the storyline)
If she hesitates and reacts like that,

00:24:52.725 --> 00:24:54.693
somehow pull her behind the counter,

00:24:54.693 --> 00:24:56.261
and make sure you get

00:24:56.261 --> 00:24:58.263
a two-shot of you and KARINA
standing together.

00:24:58.263 --> 00:25:00.199
That is your first goal as the cafe owner.

00:25:00.199 --> 00:25:01.967
Once you get that far,

00:25:01.967 --> 00:25:03.569
you've crossed the biggest...

00:25:03.569 --> 00:25:05.204
hurdle.

00:25:05.204 --> 00:25:07.706
(The key opening part is explained)

00:25:08.107 --> 00:25:11.210
(Next, they move on to another rehearsal)

00:25:11.210 --> 00:25:14.847
(Lee Eun Gyeol/Antenna trainee/Cast by Yung Suk)
I'm actually an idol trainee.

00:25:14.847 --> 00:25:16.048
(KARINA stand-in)
An actual idol trainee?

00:25:16.048 --> 00:25:17.816
An actual idol trainee.

00:25:17.816 --> 00:25:20.953
(An important scene where KARINA comes
face-to-face with her past self)

00:25:20.953 --> 00:25:22.454
Oh, if we go this far...

00:25:22.454 --> 00:25:24.189
I think KARINA will catch on.

00:25:24.189 --> 00:25:26.258
She'll think, "Oh, she's a real trainee."

00:25:26.258 --> 00:25:29.261
If she says it with that expression...

00:25:29.261 --> 00:25:31.163
By coincidence, your story

00:25:31.163 --> 00:25:33.132
is almost the same

00:25:33.132 --> 00:25:35.100
as KARINA's story before her debut.

00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:38.404
(Important role for him to cast himself)
She will probably give sincere advice.

00:25:38.404 --> 00:25:41.306
As for that,

00:25:41.306 --> 00:25:43.742
I hope you'll just speak honestly as yourself.

00:25:43.742 --> 00:25:44.576
Then...

00:25:44.576 --> 00:25:49.715
(Goal of this part, hearing heartfelt advice)
From here on, ask like she's a real senior.

00:25:50.149 --> 00:25:52.951
(The first rehearsal ends)
I'll step aside over here for a moment.

00:25:53.519 --> 00:25:55.154
Ah, is this going to work?

00:25:55.154 --> 00:25:57.256
(His nerves do not ease in this new genre)

00:25:57.256 --> 00:25:59.758
(He checks the cue sheet one more time)

00:26:03.429 --> 00:26:06.432
(Will today's shoot end well?)

00:26:07.299 --> 00:26:08.467
Hello.

00:26:08.467 --> 00:26:10.903
(The writer who helped
with the junior producer's setup came over)

00:26:11.603 --> 00:26:13.605
(Yung Suk approaches, wandering over)

00:26:15.507 --> 00:26:16.775
Later...

00:26:16.775 --> 00:26:18.277
Naevis, what was it...

00:26:18.277 --> 00:26:19.845
When sending the instructions,

00:26:19.845 --> 00:26:22.347
I'm thinking of using a laptop
instead of the phone.

00:26:22.347 --> 00:26:23.916
Shouldn't the text already be prepared

00:26:23.916 --> 00:26:25.517
so we can keep copying and pasting?

00:26:25.517 --> 00:26:27.152
Oh, we prepared the important ones like that.

00:26:27.152 --> 00:26:29.388
The important ones, the longer ones are ready.

00:26:29.388 --> 00:26:31.757
(@Monitor room)
We can do it from here.

00:26:31.757 --> 00:26:34.560
(He came to check how to send instructions)
Ju Seong, let's try sending that.

00:26:35.527 --> 00:26:36.962
Actually, I...

00:26:36.962 --> 00:26:39.031
(Including instruction delivery)
want to do a full rehearsal,

00:26:39.031 --> 00:26:40.432
but the actors have to eat...

00:26:40.432 --> 00:26:42.201
- Isn't it lunchtime for them?
- It's at 1 PM.

00:26:42.201 --> 00:26:43.202
At 1 PM?

00:26:43.202 --> 00:26:44.736
So there's still one hour until (mealtime).

00:26:44.736 --> 00:26:46.672
Oh, then...

00:26:46.672 --> 00:26:49.608
including sending in the instructions,

00:26:49.608 --> 00:26:51.910
if we run one full rehearsal,

00:26:51.910 --> 00:26:55.280
(He wants a proper full rehearsal while he can)
it'll help the camera directors as well.

00:26:55.280 --> 00:26:56.782
For KARINA's role...

00:26:56.782 --> 00:26:59.685
You can do it, or someone, you, maybe...

00:26:59.685 --> 00:27:01.353
(He plans to use a KARINA stand-in too)
Do you want to do it?

00:27:02.054 --> 00:27:03.288
- Gyeong Hee?
- Will you do it, Gyeong Hee?

00:27:03.288 --> 00:27:04.656
What do you think?
Do you want to be KARINA?

00:27:05.657 --> 00:27:06.892
- Be KARINA.
- Yes.

00:27:06.892 --> 00:27:08.760
(Ryu Gyeong Hee/Producer
/From now on, Karyuna)

00:27:08.760 --> 00:27:10.629
Let's try it like this.

00:27:10.629 --> 00:27:11.663
We'll do the rehearsal from earlier

00:27:11.663 --> 00:27:13.565
one more time, exactly the same.

00:27:13.565 --> 00:27:16.135
But in this rehearsal, directors,

00:27:16.135 --> 00:27:18.770
(KARINA stand-in)
please record all the actors

00:27:18.770 --> 00:27:20.005
reacting to and speaking to Gyeong Hee.

00:27:20.005 --> 00:27:21.106
Later,

00:27:21.106 --> 00:27:23.008
between the real take and this one,

00:27:23.008 --> 00:27:25.811
(Insert cuts are filmed during rehearsal too)
we can use whichever is better.

00:27:25.811 --> 00:27:27.746
Treat it like an actual shoot.

00:27:27.746 --> 00:27:30.849
We'll also send instructions
from the monitor room.

00:27:30.849 --> 00:27:33.519
(The second rehearsal is a full rehearsal)
That's how we'll try shooting it.

00:27:33.919 --> 00:27:36.755
(Producer Nah will be in the monitor room
as in the real shoot)

00:27:36.755 --> 00:27:41.426
(Carefully checks audio even during rehearsal)
Shouldn't we mic the KARINA role to hear her?

00:27:41.960 --> 00:27:44.696
(The actors are ready for rehearsal too)

00:27:44.696 --> 00:27:46.231
Just give me the cue to come in later,

00:27:46.231 --> 00:27:47.499
when you're ready.

00:27:47.499 --> 00:27:49.935
(Karyuna and Dr. Kim are ready too)

00:27:49.935 --> 00:27:52.971
Okay, then let's try a full rehearsal.

00:27:52.971 --> 00:27:56.308
Everyone can just stay in character.

00:27:56.308 --> 00:27:57.876
Okay, let's try it.

00:27:57.876 --> 00:27:59.611
(Cue sign)

00:27:59.611 --> 00:28:02.347
(The second rehearsal begins)

00:28:02.347 --> 00:28:04.550
(Scene 1 KARINA enters the other world)
Two iced americanos, please.

00:28:04.550 --> 00:28:06.185
Ji Min, are you kidding right now?

00:28:06.185 --> 00:28:06.919
Sorry?

00:28:06.919 --> 00:28:09.154
(The acting begins in earnest)
Hurry and get to work. Come in.

00:28:11.957 --> 00:28:14.660
(He can't even sit properly
because he's so focused)

00:28:14.660 --> 00:28:15.494
Hurry and get to work.

00:28:15.494 --> 00:28:17.062
Come in. Hurry.

00:28:17.062 --> 00:28:18.597
Come in. Hurry.

00:28:18.597 --> 00:28:19.865
Here, put this on.

00:28:24.203 --> 00:28:26.038
(Yung Suk, watching, suddenly steps forward)
This is good,

00:28:26.038 --> 00:28:28.440
but you moved behind the counter too quickly.

00:28:28.440 --> 00:28:30.709
Be a little more confused.

00:28:30.709 --> 00:28:32.277
When you put the apron on her,

00:28:32.277 --> 00:28:33.679
pull her behind the counter.

00:28:33.679 --> 00:28:35.414
KARINA probably won't even think

00:28:35.414 --> 00:28:37.449
about going in there at first.

00:28:37.449 --> 00:28:41.253
(He puts effort into this key opening part)
Show her the apron and just pull her this way...

00:28:41.253 --> 00:28:42.654
Let's try it one more time.

00:28:43.855 --> 00:28:46.525
(#4 KARINA receives the phone)
"I want to clock out." This is yours, Ji Min.

00:28:46.525 --> 00:28:47.993
Here.

00:28:47.993 --> 00:28:49.394
Make sure to check it.

00:28:49.394 --> 00:28:51.930
(This part includes sending instructions)

00:28:51.930 --> 00:28:53.498
Okay, send (the instruction).

00:28:54.066 --> 00:28:56.001
(At Producer Nah's direction,
she sent the first instruction)

00:28:56.001 --> 00:28:57.669
(Peek)

00:28:57.669 --> 00:28:59.638
(Checking if the instruction
was received properly)

00:28:59.638 --> 00:29:02.474
(#16 KARINA ends up driving)
I'll clock out now, boss.

00:29:02.474 --> 00:29:04.243
I'll park (the car).

00:29:04.243 --> 00:29:06.545
Okay, the location of the final Port Of Soul.

00:29:07.012 --> 00:29:08.981
(The rehearsal ends
with the final instruction sent)

00:29:08.981 --> 00:29:10.682
Okay, with this level of rehearsal...

00:29:10.682 --> 00:29:12.484
From the part where she gets in the car onward,

00:29:12.484 --> 00:29:13.518
I think it'll be fine.

00:29:13.518 --> 00:29:15.487
If we can film it just about this way,

00:29:15.487 --> 00:29:16.955
today's shoot will go well.

00:29:16.955 --> 00:29:17.856
It'll go well.

00:29:18.390 --> 00:29:19.558
(Anyway) thanks in advance.

00:29:19.558 --> 00:29:21.360
Great work.

00:29:21.927 --> 00:29:23.695
(Camera director)
Jeong Pyo, what do you think? If we go...

00:29:23.695 --> 00:29:25.597
like this, can you get the single shots?

00:29:25.597 --> 00:29:27.666
(He checks the cameras as soon as it ends)

00:29:27.666 --> 00:29:29.001
No matter what,

00:29:29.001 --> 00:29:30.602
KARINA's single shots are the most important.

00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:32.371
Think of this as a dramatized piece,

00:29:32.371 --> 00:29:34.172
so the actors here,

00:29:34.172 --> 00:29:36.141
we need their single shots too.

00:29:36.141 --> 00:29:36.775
Got it.

00:29:36.775 --> 00:29:39.011
(They decide to eat before filming)
Let's eat, and then prepare...

00:29:39.511 --> 00:29:41.847
(Meanwhile, at the &lt;Not the Met Gala,
but the Maetdol Gala&gt; set)

00:29:41.847 --> 00:29:43.348
They said you can go downstairs.

00:29:43.348 --> 00:29:45.550
Our filming team will go down.

00:29:46.018 --> 00:29:48.787
(Today's guest finally arrives)

00:29:48.787 --> 00:29:50.322
Hello.

00:29:50.322 --> 00:29:53.191
(The star of the first battle, aespa's KARINA)
Nice to meet you. I'm KARINA.

00:29:54.259 --> 00:29:56.528
(KARINA brought snacks for the crew herself)
Thank you.

00:29:56.528 --> 00:29:57.629
You brought us snacks.

00:29:58.196 --> 00:29:59.364
We'll enjoy them.

00:29:59.364 --> 00:30:02.134
Our &lt;Nah Yung Suk vs. Junior Producer&gt;...

00:30:02.134 --> 00:30:03.268
Yes.

00:30:03.268 --> 00:30:05.871
Thank you for agreeing so readily.

00:30:06.338 --> 00:30:09.641
(Q. How did you feel
when you first heard about the program?)

00:30:09.641 --> 00:30:11.443
It sounded like it would be fun,

00:30:11.443 --> 00:30:12.811
but honestly, I'm nervous.

00:30:13.912 --> 00:30:16.114
(Even the guest finds out on the day)
They didn't tell me anything at all.

00:30:16.848 --> 00:30:20.352
(Q. Why did you join anyway?)

00:30:20.352 --> 00:30:21.153
First of all,

00:30:21.153 --> 00:30:23.388
I really like &lt;Channel 15ya&gt;.

00:30:23.388 --> 00:30:24.589
I also like &lt;0.5ya&gt;...

00:30:24.589 --> 00:30:26.158
I like &lt;0.5ya&gt; too.

00:30:27.059 --> 00:30:28.193
That's who I am.

00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:30.329
(It turns out KARINA is a Sub too)

00:30:30.329 --> 00:30:32.931
So I really wanted to do it

00:30:32.931 --> 00:30:34.333
when the offer came in.

00:30:34.333 --> 00:30:36.468
Our first shoot will be

00:30:36.468 --> 00:30:39.971
with the junior producer, Cheon Ji In.

00:30:39.971 --> 00:30:41.707
(Q. What content do you expect?)

00:30:41.707 --> 00:30:42.941
(Thinking)

00:30:42.941 --> 00:30:44.543
What do I expect?

00:30:44.543 --> 00:30:46.611
She said there'd be some kind of party.

00:30:46.611 --> 00:30:48.280
She told me to bring a jacket.

00:30:49.081 --> 00:30:51.316
(Maetdol Gala dress code)

00:30:51.316 --> 00:30:54.353
(She definitely didn't say what kind of party)

00:30:54.353 --> 00:30:55.554
(@eggiscoming live room)
Hello.

00:30:55.554 --> 00:30:56.455
She's Producer Cheon Ji In.

00:30:56.455 --> 00:30:58.390
(The two meet for the first time)
Hello.

00:30:58.390 --> 00:31:00.092
- Hello.
- I'm Cheon Ji In.

00:31:00.092 --> 00:31:02.561
- Thanks in advance.
- Shall we sit there for a moment?

00:31:02.561 --> 00:31:04.262
(For the junior producer,
this is her first cast reading ever)

00:31:04.896 --> 00:31:06.098
(After greeting each other for the Nth time,
they sit down through the awkwardness)

00:31:06.098 --> 00:31:07.599
- Hello.
- Hello.

00:31:09.634 --> 00:31:11.370
Today, on the fourth floor,

00:31:11.370 --> 00:31:13.839
- you heard we're having a party, right?
- Yes.

00:31:13.839 --> 00:31:15.107
It is a party, right?

00:31:15.107 --> 00:31:17.042
(Suspicious to the end)
It is a party. It is.

00:31:17.042 --> 00:31:18.310
Am I partying alone?

00:31:18.310 --> 00:31:19.745
You'll be the one partying.

00:31:19.745 --> 00:31:23.315
(Entrance ticket appears)
This is the ticket you'll need to enter.

00:31:24.649 --> 00:31:27.619
(KARINA opens it right away)

00:31:29.221 --> 00:31:30.188
This is low-key annoying.

00:31:32.357 --> 00:31:35.994
(Party member, KARINA (one person))

00:31:35.994 --> 00:31:38.597
Please put on the jacket you brought

00:31:38.597 --> 00:31:40.932
and make your entrance again.

00:31:42.267 --> 00:31:43.668
It will be a bit hot, but...

00:31:43.668 --> 00:31:45.103
thanks in advance.

00:31:45.103 --> 00:31:46.972
(Bows again)

00:31:46.972 --> 00:31:49.241
(They bow deeply to each other
and the reading ends)

00:31:49.241 --> 00:31:50.208
One, two, three.

00:31:50.208 --> 00:31:51.977
(Filming begins)

00:31:52.611 --> 00:31:55.380
(KARINA enters the party venue)

00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:57.182
I feel like I should sit on my knees.

00:31:57.182 --> 00:31:59.785
Now, as you grind the millstone,

00:31:59.785 --> 00:32:02.454
please make it comfortably,
using your own recipe, KARINA.

00:32:02.454 --> 00:32:04.689
(The shoot proceeds calmly)
That's all you need to do.

00:32:04.689 --> 00:32:07.125
Ah, the black (beans).

00:32:07.125 --> 00:32:07.993
Actually, I was just

00:32:07.993 --> 00:32:10.929
asking Gemini for a recipe.

00:32:10.929 --> 00:32:12.898
First, tell me how to make soy milk noodles.

00:32:14.332 --> 00:32:16.301
The top recommended combination is

00:32:16.301 --> 00:32:18.437
basil, arugula, and chili

00:32:18.437 --> 00:32:20.338
for Italian-fusion soy milk noodles.

00:32:20.338 --> 00:32:22.007
(A never-before-seen recipe appears)

00:32:22.007 --> 00:32:25.043
(Joking)
Ah, I wasn't planning to make it this good.

00:32:25.043 --> 00:32:27.446
Then I'll go with
Italian fusion soy milk noodles.

00:32:28.847 --> 00:32:30.715
(Recipe saved for now)

00:32:30.715 --> 00:32:31.716
This will be fun.

00:32:31.716 --> 00:32:34.186
(A dish to look forward to
thanks to the fresh recipe)

00:32:34.186 --> 00:32:36.655
(The Maetdol Gala party begins in earnest)

00:32:36.655 --> 00:32:38.356
Here's the first quiz.

00:32:38.356 --> 00:32:40.792
The Maet-ter is,

00:32:40.792 --> 00:32:42.561
how old is KARINA?

00:32:43.528 --> 00:32:46.898
(The shoot keeps the fun mood they intended)

00:32:46.898 --> 00:32:48.099
(Meanwhile, before they know it)

00:32:48.099 --> 00:32:51.136
Producer Cheon,
we have 40 minutes of filming time left.

00:32:51.670 --> 00:32:54.039
(Their allotted filming time is running out)

00:32:55.140 --> 00:32:57.275
(Producer Cheon Ji In adjusts
the second half on the spot)

00:32:57.275 --> 00:33:01.079
Let's do one or two questions she can answer,

00:33:01.079 --> 00:33:02.814
and then stop (grinding the millstone).

00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:05.116
Stop grinding? Then...

00:33:05.116 --> 00:33:06.485
I think we're good.

00:33:06.485 --> 00:33:08.620
(Before they know it,
the soybean broth is ready)

00:33:09.554 --> 00:33:12.591
(While KARINA goes to the garden
to pick ingredients)

00:33:12.591 --> 00:33:15.827
Should we put a handheld cam in the garden?

00:33:15.827 --> 00:33:16.962
A fixed cam?

00:33:16.962 --> 00:33:19.498
Would it be better
for the camera directors to follow her?

00:33:19.498 --> 00:33:20.632
Should we just cover one angle?

00:33:21.099 --> 00:33:23.768
(She checks every detail
despite the tight schedule)

00:33:24.469 --> 00:33:26.304
(Installing an additional camera)

00:33:26.304 --> 00:33:29.040
(Thanks to that, they got more varied cuts)

00:33:30.075 --> 00:33:32.577
(Meanwhile, KARINA's soy milk noodles
are completed)

00:33:32.577 --> 00:33:34.079
It's so much better than we expected.

00:33:34.079 --> 00:33:35.013
Exactly.

00:33:36.214 --> 00:33:37.682
Does it spin?

00:33:37.682 --> 00:33:40.385
(Before they know it,
only the final segment remains)

00:33:40.385 --> 00:33:41.419
Once she gets the sticker,

00:33:41.419 --> 00:33:42.687
if she puts (the noodles) right here,

00:33:42.687 --> 00:33:43.622
(the turntable) spins.

00:33:44.055 --> 00:33:47.792
(The photo wall setup check is done too)

00:33:47.792 --> 00:33:49.394
Okay, photographers, did you get nice shots?

00:33:49.394 --> 00:33:50.095
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:33:50.095 --> 00:33:52.931
All right, then the soy milk noodles debut

00:33:52.931 --> 00:33:53.665
is a success.

00:33:53.665 --> 00:33:55.200
Success.

00:33:56.167 --> 00:33:57.235
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

00:33:57.235 --> 00:33:58.537
(Thankfully, all filming finished on time)

00:33:58.537 --> 00:34:00.005
Phew, great job.

00:34:00.005 --> 00:34:01.806
No problem. It was fun.

00:34:03.241 --> 00:34:05.310
Why does it look so pretty spinning?

00:34:05.310 --> 00:34:07.946
(I can't stop looking at my soy milk noodles)

00:34:08.747 --> 00:34:11.650
(She takes a commemorative photo herself)

00:34:11.650 --> 00:34:14.352
(Q. How did you feel filming
&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;?)

00:34:14.352 --> 00:34:19.157
It was something I'd never experienced before.

00:34:19.157 --> 00:34:22.594
You don't often get to grind a millstone
on a wooden platform,

00:34:22.594 --> 00:34:26.131
and having a meal...

00:34:26.131 --> 00:34:28.333
with a CEO from another company was new too.

00:34:28.333 --> 00:34:29.167
It was just so much fun.

00:34:29.167 --> 00:34:30.535
The weather was great,

00:34:30.535 --> 00:34:31.436
and it was fun.

00:34:31.436 --> 00:34:33.138
I...

00:34:33.138 --> 00:34:34.472
(Whispering)
think she'll win.

00:34:34.472 --> 00:34:36.608
I think the junior producer will win.

00:34:36.608 --> 00:34:38.610
I haven't done (Yung Suk's shoot) yet,

00:34:38.610 --> 00:34:39.678
but so far.

00:34:40.946 --> 00:34:43.114
(The two meet again)

00:34:43.114 --> 00:34:47.152
When I become a big-time producer
in ten years, I'll come back...

00:34:48.520 --> 00:34:50.355
- You can do it.
- Thank you.

00:34:50.355 --> 00:34:53.825
Ji In was born in 2001.

00:34:54.359 --> 00:34:55.660
(One year younger than KARINA)

00:34:55.660 --> 00:34:57.062
Call me sis.

00:34:57.062 --> 00:34:58.396
(Full sister energy)

00:34:58.396 --> 00:35:01.633
- You rarely work with a younger producer.
- Exactly.

00:35:01.633 --> 00:35:03.969
(This shoot must have been special
for both of them)

00:35:03.969 --> 00:35:05.670
(Good luck)

00:35:05.670 --> 00:35:07.038
She says you'll win.

00:35:07.038 --> 00:35:08.039
Really?

00:35:08.039 --> 00:35:09.608
I haven't done it with Producer Nah yet,

00:35:09.608 --> 00:35:11.076
but so far, it's 1 to 0.

00:35:11.476 --> 00:35:14.679
(KARINA supports the junior producer to the end)

00:35:15.547 --> 00:35:16.548
Thank you.

00:35:16.548 --> 00:35:17.816
Great work today.

00:35:17.816 --> 00:35:20.852
(The shoot wraps safely)

00:35:20.852 --> 00:35:24.322
Today was the day the plan

00:35:24.322 --> 00:35:26.257
you and Gemini created together came to life.

00:35:26.758 --> 00:35:28.159
(Q. How do you feel about the shoot?)

00:35:28.159 --> 00:35:29.928
First, I feel so relieved.

00:35:29.928 --> 00:35:31.696
I couldn't sleep properly yesterday,

00:35:31.696 --> 00:35:35.433
but starting today,
I think I can finally sleep easy.

00:35:35.433 --> 00:35:37.268
And...

00:35:37.268 --> 00:35:40.538
this almost purely imaginary story...

00:35:40.538 --> 00:35:42.941
called &lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;

00:35:42.941 --> 00:35:46.444
came to life today

00:35:46.444 --> 00:35:48.346
thanks to everyone who worked hard with me.

00:35:48.346 --> 00:35:51.349
All the producers, writers, and directors,

00:35:51.349 --> 00:35:53.551
(Bowing for the Nth time today)
thank you. Thank you so much.

00:35:53.551 --> 00:35:55.550
(A day she was grateful to many people)
It's basically an acceptance speech.

00:35:55.854 --> 00:35:57.422
- Great work.
- Thank you.

00:36:00.659 --> 00:36:04.362
(&lt;Not the Met Gala, but the Maetdol Gala&gt;
shoot wraps)

00:36:04.929 --> 00:36:07.065
(Meanwhile, at Producer Nah's set)

00:36:07.065 --> 00:36:09.170
(After the meal, a short break)

00:36:09.601 --> 00:36:11.002
(Staring)

00:36:11.002 --> 00:36:12.037
Is that Da Som?

00:36:13.038 --> 00:36:14.839
(The writer who finished
the junior producer's shoot came over)

00:36:14.839 --> 00:36:16.174
Why does Da Som look so...

00:36:16.174 --> 00:36:17.509
Why is she back looking like that?

00:36:17.509 --> 00:36:18.643
(A little exhausted)

00:36:18.643 --> 00:36:19.711
Are you okay?

00:36:19.711 --> 00:36:20.679
Wow, you worked hard.

00:36:21.513 --> 00:36:23.214
Did (the &lt;Maetdol Gala&gt; shoot) go well?

00:36:23.214 --> 00:36:24.249
Who knows?

00:36:24.249 --> 00:36:25.250
(Oh)

00:36:25.251 --> 00:36:27.018
Why are you trying so hard to keep it secret?

00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:28.953
(Pressed)
I mean, is this...

00:36:28.953 --> 00:36:29.888
classified?

00:36:29.888 --> 00:36:30.789
I mean...

00:36:30.789 --> 00:36:32.657
I thought you might get nervous
for the second half.

00:36:32.657 --> 00:36:33.658
Oh, me?

00:36:33.658 --> 00:36:34.659
It went well, didn't it?

00:36:34.659 --> 00:36:35.994
- It must've gone well.
- Oh, so it went well.

00:36:35.994 --> 00:36:37.262
Haha.

00:36:37.262 --> 00:36:38.663
(Anxiety)
I guess it went well.

00:36:38.663 --> 00:36:40.165
(Keeping the rival in check)
Ah, I guess it was fun.

00:36:40.165 --> 00:36:41.599
But that...

00:36:41.599 --> 00:36:42.667
Should we call it successful?

00:36:44.335 --> 00:36:45.336
Ah...

00:36:45.336 --> 00:36:47.539
(He has been properly pressed)
She seems happy. She came back happy.

00:36:49.808 --> 00:36:51.176
Hey, but...

00:36:51.176 --> 00:36:52.610
I'm being really, really honest.

00:36:52.610 --> 00:36:54.679
I'm nervous for the first time in so long.

00:36:54.679 --> 00:36:56.047
(The 26-year veteran is shaken)

00:36:56.047 --> 00:36:56.948
Now,

00:36:56.948 --> 00:36:58.450
seeing Da Som's expression...

00:36:58.450 --> 00:36:59.484
Hmm.

00:36:59.951 --> 00:37:02.320
(He grows anxious
as the junior team seems to have done well)

00:37:02.320 --> 00:37:04.956
(Suddenly, his throat feels dry)

00:37:04.956 --> 00:37:06.391
(Current time, 2:20 PM)

00:37:06.391 --> 00:37:09.828
(Ten minutes before filming starts)

00:37:09.828 --> 00:37:12.597
(As filming approaches,
he has a lot on his mind)

00:37:12.597 --> 00:37:14.566
Sir, could we...

00:37:14.566 --> 00:37:15.867
run through it again, just roughly,

00:37:15.867 --> 00:37:16.701
one more time?

00:37:16.701 --> 00:37:18.136
Oh, that'd be great.

00:37:18.136 --> 00:37:20.338
(He's asked for one last rehearsal)

00:37:20.338 --> 00:37:21.439
I was actually thinking

00:37:21.439 --> 00:37:22.707
maybe...

00:37:22.707 --> 00:37:24.476
we should try it one more time.

00:37:24.476 --> 00:37:26.911
(Third rehearsal)

00:37:26.911 --> 00:37:29.047
(#1 KARINA enters the alternate world)
Iced americano...

00:37:29.047 --> 00:37:31.282
(#7 Explaining compliment stickers)
One compliment sticker from customers.

00:37:31.282 --> 00:37:33.384
(#9 KARINA celebrates the couple's anniversary)
That's so nice.

00:37:33.384 --> 00:37:35.820
(#10 KARINA helps the office worker with a poem)
His name is Rhee Myung Han.

00:37:36.354 --> 00:37:39.691
(The third rehearsal moves along quickly)

00:37:40.792 --> 00:37:43.728
(As they race through the rehearsal,)

00:37:43.728 --> 00:37:46.164
(the crew arrives to start filming)

00:37:48.466 --> 00:37:50.101
We'll just... stop (the rehearsal) here and go.

00:37:50.101 --> 00:37:51.536
I think that'd be better too.

00:37:52.403 --> 00:37:55.206
(2:30 PM, the promised filming time approaches)
Compared to the others, I'm still inexperienced

00:37:55.206 --> 00:37:58.176
and I tend to struggle with it.

00:37:59.210 --> 00:38:00.445
(Pretends not to notice)
Ah, dancing...

00:38:00.445 --> 00:38:02.347
You're a bit weak at dancing.

00:38:02.347 --> 00:38:04.949
(Stubbornly)
You had a bit of a hard time...

00:38:04.949 --> 00:38:06.651
(Pushes on with rehearsal, perhaps from nerves)
Has that happened before?

00:38:06.651 --> 00:38:08.153
We'll stop here.

00:38:08.153 --> 00:38:10.688
(They eventually stop the rehearsal)

00:38:10.688 --> 00:38:13.591
(Now it really is time to film)

00:38:13.591 --> 00:38:15.393
(After three rounds of rehearsal)
Please leave enough time to get reactions...

00:38:15.393 --> 00:38:16.895
After she gets the message...

00:38:16.895 --> 00:38:18.997
Which way is Hakdong Station?

00:38:18.997 --> 00:38:21.332
If she circles around and comes back here, I...

00:38:21.332 --> 00:38:23.968
(He changes ending location for the shot)
Maybe we'll change it like that.

00:38:23.968 --> 00:38:25.904
Jeong Pyo, what do you think?
If we go like this...

00:38:25.904 --> 00:38:27.739
(Camera movement is also checked)
can you get the single shots?

00:38:28.406 --> 00:38:30.208
(Producer Nah has finished all preparations)

00:38:30.208 --> 00:38:32.010
(Nervous)

00:38:32.677 --> 00:38:35.113
(The set grows tense too)

00:38:35.113 --> 00:38:35.947
Are we going?

00:38:35.947 --> 00:38:36.948
Are we going by car?

00:38:36.948 --> 00:38:38.016
We'll take this car

00:38:38.016 --> 00:38:39.684
and come right back.

00:38:39.684 --> 00:38:40.952
I get out of the car,
briefly say hello to KARINA,

00:38:40.952 --> 00:38:41.686
and get in, right?

00:38:41.686 --> 00:38:43.288
Then we do the briefing in the live room.

00:38:43.922 --> 00:38:47.358
(Current time, 2:30 PM)

00:38:47.358 --> 00:38:50.628
(Leaving for the shoot)

00:38:50.628 --> 00:38:53.431
(@eggiscoming)

00:38:53.431 --> 00:38:55.233
(They arrive at the company)

00:38:55.800 --> 00:38:57.435
Where is she? I'll just go to the restroom...

00:38:57.435 --> 00:38:58.970
and I'll come down.

00:38:58.970 --> 00:39:01.973
(He looks for the restroom first,
perhaps from nerves)

00:39:01.973 --> 00:39:04.108
(@Live room)

00:39:04.108 --> 00:39:05.810
I didn't know we'd be going (outside).

00:39:05.810 --> 00:39:08.413
(KARINA is waiting for Producer Nah)

00:39:08.413 --> 00:39:09.681
Director, do you know everything

00:39:09.681 --> 00:39:10.815
about what we're doing?

00:39:10.815 --> 00:39:12.784
(She seems anxious
with no information about the shoot)

00:39:12.784 --> 00:39:14.385
(Desperate)
Do you know?

00:39:16.254 --> 00:39:17.622
(Producer Nah enters just in time)
You must be so tired.

00:39:17.622 --> 00:39:18.857
It's been a lot, right?

00:39:18.857 --> 00:39:20.425
When did you get back to (Korea)?
Take a seat.

00:39:20.425 --> 00:39:21.593
I got back to Korea the day before yesterday.

00:39:21.593 --> 00:39:22.560
- The day before yesterday?
- Yes.

00:39:22.560 --> 00:39:23.294
After Mexico...

00:39:23.294 --> 00:39:24.329
How long were you there?

00:39:24.329 --> 00:39:26.097
Three days?

00:39:26.097 --> 00:39:27.970
(He starts with small talk to lighten the mood)
Two days in Mexico.

00:39:28.533 --> 00:39:30.535
Mm...

00:39:30.535 --> 00:39:33.238
As you know, I...

00:39:33.238 --> 00:39:35.039
am now with a junior producer

00:39:35.039 --> 00:39:37.642
(Producer Nah gets to the point)
in a kind of battle.

00:39:37.642 --> 00:39:39.277
- It was fun.
- I was hoping the first shoot would go badly...

00:39:39.277 --> 00:39:40.011
It was fun?

00:39:40.011 --> 00:39:42.146
- It was fun.
- Ah...

00:39:42.146 --> 00:39:43.648
Now I'm nervous.

00:39:43.648 --> 00:39:45.550
(He loses confidence before even starting)

00:39:45.550 --> 00:39:48.219
I may have made a mistake...

00:39:48.219 --> 00:39:49.420
(Not her problem)

00:39:49.420 --> 00:39:52.490
Is my 25-year career crumbling here?

00:39:52.490 --> 00:39:53.958
(Belated regret)

00:39:53.958 --> 00:39:54.926
(Checks again)
Did you enjoy it?

00:39:54.926 --> 00:39:55.860
(Final confirmation)
I enjoyed it.

00:39:55.860 --> 00:39:58.363
She said she'd trample you and climb over you...

00:39:59.797 --> 00:40:01.799
(He's intimidated again by his bold junior)

00:40:01.799 --> 00:40:02.600
Oh, this is bad.

00:40:02.600 --> 00:40:05.103
This might be my last shoot.

00:40:05.103 --> 00:40:07.572
You might be my last guest.

00:40:07.572 --> 00:40:08.907
The finale.

00:40:08.907 --> 00:40:11.576
(First, he explains the creative intent)
Let me explain the background just a little.

00:40:11.576 --> 00:40:14.145
When we filmed &lt;Chattering with Nah&gt; together,

00:40:14.145 --> 00:40:16.648
you talked about those hard memories
from when you were 21.

00:40:16.648 --> 00:40:17.782
Back then...

00:40:17.782 --> 00:40:20.518
you briefly said things like,
"My life feels stuck on that day."

00:40:20.518 --> 00:40:22.487
We briefly talked about that, remember?

00:40:22.487 --> 00:40:24.088
I actually took inspiration from that

00:40:24.088 --> 00:40:25.690
and made this program.

00:40:25.690 --> 00:40:27.425
Just two things.

00:40:27.425 --> 00:40:29.394
(Final requests before he steps out)
I'll ask you here, then step out.

00:40:29.394 --> 00:40:30.461
First,

00:40:30.461 --> 00:40:32.530
while you're filming, you'll get a phone.

00:40:32.530 --> 00:40:33.231
Yes.

00:40:33.231 --> 00:40:35.800
Please keep that phone with you,

00:40:35.800 --> 00:40:37.969
and pay close attention to the messages.

00:40:37.969 --> 00:40:39.570
Don't put it down.

00:40:39.570 --> 00:40:40.905
Second,

00:40:40.905 --> 00:40:42.040
uh...

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:43.274
Well, that's it.

00:40:44.475 --> 00:40:45.510
Second, uh, well...

00:40:45.510 --> 00:40:46.644
Don't panic, just...

00:40:46.644 --> 00:40:48.012
No quitting halfway?

00:40:48.012 --> 00:40:49.113
You said you like games and things, right?

00:40:49.113 --> 00:40:49.781
I do.

00:40:49.781 --> 00:40:51.215
You like games and &lt;Infinite Challenge&gt;, right?

00:40:51.215 --> 00:40:52.116
Didn't you grow up
watching &lt;Infinite Challenge&gt;?

00:40:52.116 --> 00:40:54.319
(Don't say that)

00:40:54.319 --> 00:40:55.453
&lt;Infinite Challenge&gt;, of course.

00:40:55.453 --> 00:40:57.355
(Petty)
You're totally an &lt;Infinite Challenge&gt; kid.

00:40:57.355 --> 00:40:59.257
No, I'm not.

00:40:59.257 --> 00:41:00.658
Uh, anyway,

00:41:00.658 --> 00:41:02.427
just think of it as having

00:41:02.427 --> 00:41:04.896
(One last request for smooth filming)
a fun experience for about an hour.

00:41:04.896 --> 00:41:06.230
Shall we go?

00:41:06.230 --> 00:41:06.864
Let's go.

00:41:06.864 --> 00:41:09.300
Please tell them we're headed that way.

00:41:09.300 --> 00:41:12.203
(Filming begins)

00:41:12.203 --> 00:41:13.271
Ah...

00:41:13.271 --> 00:41:15.139
What if I lose to Ji In?

00:41:15.139 --> 00:41:17.475
(He gets into the car first, nervous)

00:41:17.475 --> 00:41:19.210
Oh wow.

00:41:19.210 --> 00:41:22.280
(KARINA gets into the car after him)

00:41:22.280 --> 00:41:24.115
Is this car for a Class 2 or Class 1 license?

00:41:25.516 --> 00:41:27.852
(KARINA shows interest in the car first)
Look at her.

00:41:27.852 --> 00:41:29.320
Have you practiced (driving) since then?

00:41:29.320 --> 00:41:31.122
Just once yesterday.

00:41:31.122 --> 00:41:32.190
In what kind of car?

00:41:32.190 --> 00:41:33.157
A Carnival.

00:41:33.157 --> 00:41:34.759
(He subtly asks about driving too)
A company car?

00:41:34.759 --> 00:41:35.927
How was it?

00:41:35.927 --> 00:41:38.029
I was really good.

00:41:38.029 --> 00:41:40.198
I was amazing.

00:41:40.198 --> 00:41:41.699
Okay, we're off.

00:41:43.501 --> 00:41:47.005
(Finally, he takes KARINA
into the alternate world)

00:41:47.005 --> 00:41:49.540
(@Back at the cafe)

00:41:49.540 --> 00:41:52.210
(The actors wait
after getting the departure notice)

00:41:52.210 --> 00:41:54.312
(The car arrives right on cue)

00:41:55.380 --> 00:41:57.348
(KARINA gets out of the car to buy coffee)

00:41:57.348 --> 00:41:58.816
(Go ahead)

00:41:58.816 --> 00:42:00.651
(Producer Nah gets out after her)

00:42:01.819 --> 00:42:03.554
(He carefully enters
without disrupting the shoot)

00:42:05.123 --> 00:42:07.625
(Arrives at the monitor room)

00:42:07.625 --> 00:42:09.260
Where are we?

00:42:09.260 --> 00:42:10.928
She just ordered the iced americano.

00:42:10.928 --> 00:42:12.930
(After checking the situation)

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:15.366
(He immediately focuses on monitoring)

00:42:15.833 --> 00:42:17.869
(#1 KARINA orders coffee)
You're always late.

00:42:17.869 --> 00:42:19.270
Huh?

00:42:19.270 --> 00:42:21.105
Really?

00:42:21.105 --> 00:42:21.973
Hey.

00:42:21.973 --> 00:42:23.408
Seriously? Really?

00:42:26.811 --> 00:42:29.080
(Still unable to relax)

00:42:29.080 --> 00:42:30.782
Look at this.

00:42:30.782 --> 00:42:32.350
- "Yoo Ji Min."
- Oh.

00:42:32.350 --> 00:42:35.086
(It seems to be going smoothly)
You worked here all month. What are you saying?

00:42:36.154 --> 00:42:38.923
(Yung Suk is somehow tense)

00:42:38.923 --> 00:42:40.258
Only when you put the apron on her,

00:42:40.258 --> 00:42:41.559
pull her in here.

00:42:41.559 --> 00:42:43.461
KARINA probably won't even think

00:42:43.461 --> 00:42:45.430
about going in there at first.

00:42:45.430 --> 00:42:48.800
(The reality-alternate world connection)
Show her the apron and just pull her that way...

00:42:48.800 --> 00:42:51.669
(Will KARINA accept the alternate world?)
You not showing up to work is the accident.

00:42:51.669 --> 00:42:52.770
Put it on, hurry. Here.

00:42:52.770 --> 00:42:54.505
Here.

00:42:54.505 --> 00:42:55.973
Thank you. Are you the cafe owner?

00:42:55.973 --> 00:42:57.642
(Almost too easy)
Of course. It says so here.

00:42:57.642 --> 00:42:58.509
"Yoo Ji Min."

00:42:59.077 --> 00:43:00.211
Ah.

00:43:00.211 --> 00:43:02.246
(Producer Nah finally smiles)

00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:03.614
(#4 KARINA receives the phone)
This looks like yours, Ji Min.

00:43:03.614 --> 00:43:04.816
Messages keep coming in.

00:43:04.816 --> 00:43:05.750
That's your phone, Ji Min.

00:43:05.750 --> 00:43:07.318
Yes, it is mine...

00:43:08.152 --> 00:43:10.588
(The timing to send
the first instruction is near)

00:43:10.588 --> 00:43:11.489
Send (the instruction).

00:43:12.190 --> 00:43:14.892
(Alarm rings)

00:43:14.892 --> 00:43:16.894
This is so annoying.

00:43:16.894 --> 00:43:17.728
(Proud)
Heehee.

00:43:17.728 --> 00:43:19.297
She says it's so annoying.

00:43:19.297 --> 00:43:21.032
(The reaction is more satisfying than expected)

00:43:21.499 --> 00:43:23.835
How do I clock out?

00:43:23.835 --> 00:43:27.672
Boss, I want to clock out.

00:43:27.672 --> 00:43:29.607
(Asks to clock out even without instructions)
What time do I clock out?

00:43:29.607 --> 00:43:31.342
Good, we don't need the second...

00:43:31.342 --> 00:43:33.044
We don't need the second instruction.

00:43:33.044 --> 00:43:35.546
Play the (news) video.

00:43:35.546 --> 00:43:38.549
(Yung Suk forgot the news cue)
If you give the play-video cue, I'll play it.

00:43:38.549 --> 00:43:39.750
Please play the (news) video.

00:43:39.750 --> 00:43:41.185
(Signal delivered)

00:43:41.886 --> 00:43:43.054
I'm now, oh...

00:43:44.689 --> 00:43:46.958
(Thankfully, the video plays just in time)

00:43:46.958 --> 00:43:48.092
Ohoho.

00:43:48.092 --> 00:43:49.393
Heehee.

00:43:50.828 --> 00:43:53.030
(He forgot, but things keep moving smoothly)

00:43:53.030 --> 00:43:55.700
(#11 KARINA takes out the trash)
I think

00:43:55.700 --> 00:43:57.101
she'll put (the sticker) on in five minutes.

00:43:57.101 --> 00:43:58.369
Five minutes.

00:43:58.369 --> 00:44:00.138
What about that gentleman?

00:44:01.172 --> 00:44:04.375
(The cafe owner is supposed to
ask KARINA to take out the trash)

00:44:04.375 --> 00:44:05.776
Hmm.

00:44:05.776 --> 00:44:07.678
Boss...

00:44:09.180 --> 00:44:13.217
(He seems to have forgotten the trash request)
Is she a trainee or something?

00:44:13.217 --> 00:44:15.319
Trash, trash, trash, trash.

00:44:15.319 --> 00:44:17.088
He forgot the trash bag.

00:44:17.088 --> 00:44:18.823
The cafe owner forgot.

00:44:18.823 --> 00:44:20.124
Ah, suddenly...

00:44:20.124 --> 00:44:21.592
He forgot.

00:44:21.592 --> 00:44:23.127
The cafe owner forgot.

00:44:23.127 --> 00:44:25.096
(He hurries to signal the cafe owner)

00:44:25.096 --> 00:44:26.030
Hey.

00:44:27.598 --> 00:44:28.833
Trash.

00:44:28.833 --> 00:44:30.468
Trash.

00:44:30.468 --> 00:44:31.369
Trash.

00:44:34.238 --> 00:44:35.439
Ah...

00:44:35.439 --> 00:44:37.808
(He finally catches on)
Ji Min, come here.

00:44:37.808 --> 00:44:38.776
This...

00:44:38.776 --> 00:44:40.178
Could you take out the trash?

00:44:40.178 --> 00:44:41.145
Oh, the trash.

00:44:42.113 --> 00:44:43.214
Ah.

00:44:43.848 --> 00:44:46.484
(This crisis passes smoothly too)

00:44:46.484 --> 00:44:49.220
(#17 KARINA drives)
Then I'll move the car for you.

00:44:49.220 --> 00:44:50.288
Oh, sure.

00:44:50.288 --> 00:44:52.590
Then I'll leave now.

00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:55.059
(KARINA leaves to drive)

00:44:55.059 --> 00:44:56.294
(Jumps up)

00:44:56.294 --> 00:44:58.729
(He follows to check the outside situation)

00:44:58.729 --> 00:45:00.731
(The driving part
he had looked forward to since planning)

00:45:00.731 --> 00:45:01.599
Ah...

00:45:02.934 --> 00:45:06.704
(The car departs with everyone focused)
Okay, okay, good, good.

00:45:06.704 --> 00:45:08.206
She'll be back in three minutes.

00:45:08.206 --> 00:45:09.640
You all did so well.

00:45:09.640 --> 00:45:11.108
Everyone did so well.

00:45:11.108 --> 00:45:11.976
Thank you.

00:45:11.976 --> 00:45:13.844
Now we just need to finish well.

00:45:13.844 --> 00:45:15.112
Please stay seated,

00:45:15.112 --> 00:45:17.949
then later follow the cafe owner outside.

00:45:17.949 --> 00:45:20.117
All go out and say, "What's wrong with her?"

00:45:20.117 --> 00:45:22.186
(He rechecks the ending movement)
You just need to do that well.

00:45:22.186 --> 00:45:24.422
(This instruction) should go out
around when she arrives.

00:45:24.422 --> 00:45:26.657
(He checks the final instruction once more)

00:45:26.657 --> 00:45:27.658
Okay.

00:45:29.327 --> 00:45:31.896
(Meanwhile,
the car is rounding the final corner)

00:45:32.897 --> 00:45:34.432
(She's almost here)

00:45:34.432 --> 00:45:35.533
She's here, she's here, she's here.

00:45:37.201 --> 00:45:39.704
Okay, just watch for the beeping.

00:45:39.704 --> 00:45:40.938
Very good.

00:45:40.938 --> 00:45:42.206
(She attempts the difficult parking maneuver)

00:45:42.206 --> 00:45:44.141
Okay, straighten up and back up slowly.

00:45:45.743 --> 00:45:46.644
Uh, uh...

00:45:47.979 --> 00:45:49.013
Uhh...

00:45:49.013 --> 00:45:50.348
Uhhhhhh.

00:45:52.149 --> 00:45:54.552
Ah...

00:45:54.552 --> 00:45:57.421
(For the first time in ages,
he nearly aged ten years on set)

00:45:57.421 --> 00:45:59.557
(#18 KARINA shouts at the P.O.S)

00:45:59.557 --> 00:46:01.125
They're making me embarrass myself.

00:46:03.027 --> 00:46:04.128
Okay, let's go.

00:46:04.128 --> 00:46:05.363
Please say, "What's wrong with her?"

00:46:06.197 --> 00:46:08.666
(The cafe owner moves
at Producer Nah's direction)

00:46:08.666 --> 00:46:09.867
What is she doing?

00:46:10.534 --> 00:46:11.969
(The others move too)

00:46:11.969 --> 00:46:13.170
She's doing something weird.

00:46:14.605 --> 00:46:16.207
(The other actors begin acting too)
Isn't that the part-timer from earlier?

00:46:16.207 --> 00:46:17.742
Oh, you're right.

00:46:17.742 --> 00:46:19.477
Yes, she's the part-timer here.

00:46:19.477 --> 00:46:20.811
Go outside.

00:46:23.447 --> 00:46:25.916
(The actors come outside
at Producer Nah's direction)

00:46:27.084 --> 00:46:30.554
(#19 Ending)
Anarika ma I.

00:46:30.554 --> 00:46:31.689
Huh? Isn't that KARINA?

00:46:31.689 --> 00:46:34.025
Oh, KARINA. No way.

00:46:34.025 --> 00:46:36.961
(The actors start acting
as if they recognize KARINA)

00:46:37.728 --> 00:46:40.398
(Producer Nah uses the moment
to step outside and wrap up)

00:46:44.535 --> 00:46:47.204
(He watches the reaction
a little longer from afar)

00:46:48.272 --> 00:46:49.674
KARINA.

00:46:49.674 --> 00:46:50.741
KARINA.

00:46:50.741 --> 00:46:52.476
You said you were going to buy coffee,

00:46:52.476 --> 00:46:54.111
- Right.
- so why are you here?

00:46:54.111 --> 00:46:56.847
(And just like that, the alternate world ends)

00:46:56.847 --> 00:46:58.349
Yes.

00:46:58.349 --> 00:47:01.252
(Now it's time to end filming)

00:47:01.252 --> 00:47:02.186
Okay, that's it.

00:47:02.186 --> 00:47:05.956
- Great work.
- Great work.

00:47:05.956 --> 00:47:07.425
Oh, that was fun...

00:47:07.425 --> 00:47:09.760
- Great work.
- Great work.

00:47:09.760 --> 00:47:12.496
(Thankfully, the shoot wrapped safely)
Okay, let's go inside and wrap up.

00:47:12.496 --> 00:47:14.231
Great work. You're good.

00:47:14.231 --> 00:47:15.833
No, I'm not.

00:47:15.833 --> 00:47:17.268
Wow, you're good.

00:47:17.268 --> 00:47:19.403
You were so much more...

00:47:19.403 --> 00:47:21.472
(Impressed)
natural playing along than I expected.

00:47:21.472 --> 00:47:22.973
(Producer Nah is quite satisfied with the shoot)

00:47:22.973 --> 00:47:23.908
I'm exhausted.

00:47:23.908 --> 00:47:24.975
Thank you for singing for us.

00:47:24.975 --> 00:47:27.144
- Not at all.
- I really didn't mean to keep a straight face.

00:47:27.144 --> 00:47:28.879
I couldn't hold back.

00:47:28.879 --> 00:47:29.947
(The actors belatedly offer explanations
that aren't quite explanations)

00:47:29.947 --> 00:47:31.282
You worked so hard.

00:47:31.282 --> 00:47:32.450
Are you really a trainee?

00:47:32.450 --> 00:47:33.884
- Yes, I'm really a trainee.
- Really?

00:47:33.884 --> 00:47:35.820
Oh my.

00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:37.655
I'm really not a cult recruiter.

00:47:39.690 --> 00:47:40.624
(No way)

00:47:40.624 --> 00:47:41.559
A side job?

00:47:42.560 --> 00:47:45.463
(&lt;I'm KARINA In Real Life, But In An Alternate
World, I'm 21-Year-Old Ji Min?&gt; shoot wraps)

00:47:46.530 --> 00:47:48.532
Today's Nah Yung Suk vs. Junior Producer shoot

00:47:48.532 --> 00:47:49.800
wraps here.

00:47:49.800 --> 00:47:51.736
Wow, great work.

00:47:53.104 --> 00:47:56.507
(Filming ends)

00:47:57.842 --> 00:48:00.811
(Q. How did you feel about today's shoot?)

00:48:00.811 --> 00:48:02.780
It was fun.

00:48:02.780 --> 00:48:04.715
I've been a producer for 25 years,

00:48:04.715 --> 00:48:05.916
but today's shoot

00:48:05.916 --> 00:48:08.719
was something I'd never done before.

00:48:09.320 --> 00:48:10.354
The one thing I regret is,

00:48:10.354 --> 00:48:12.089
since it's a variety show,

00:48:12.089 --> 00:48:13.257
we had to include funny situations,

00:48:13.257 --> 00:48:15.025
and as we added this and that,

00:48:15.025 --> 00:48:18.396
the narrative immersion
seems to have dropped a bit.

00:48:18.396 --> 00:48:19.897
But it was still fun.

00:48:19.897 --> 00:48:21.332
I'm satisfied.

00:48:21.332 --> 00:48:23.901
(Q. What would you change for the next battle?)

00:48:23.901 --> 00:48:25.936
When a guest comes on,

00:48:25.936 --> 00:48:27.204
that guest...

00:48:27.204 --> 00:48:28.739
something that guest might like,

00:48:28.739 --> 00:48:29.640
or something...

00:48:29.640 --> 00:48:31.742
they might want to do. I'll think about that

00:48:31.742 --> 00:48:34.545
and try that.

00:48:34.545 --> 00:48:36.213
I really never imagined

00:48:36.213 --> 00:48:37.915
we'd do something like this.

00:48:37.915 --> 00:48:38.883
I...

00:48:38.883 --> 00:48:40.684
Whether I did well...

00:48:40.684 --> 00:48:42.052
I don't remember

00:48:42.052 --> 00:48:42.987
right now.

00:48:42.987 --> 00:48:44.121
Oh, but...

00:48:44.121 --> 00:48:47.992
I'm so curious
what the next guests will be asked to do.

00:48:47.992 --> 00:48:49.460
You worked so hard today.

00:48:49.460 --> 00:48:50.394
It was fun.

00:48:50.394 --> 00:48:52.596
(A message to KARINA, who worked hard today)
It was fun? That's a relief.

00:48:52.596 --> 00:48:54.732
Even though it was quite flustering too.

00:48:54.732 --> 00:48:57.034
But you didn't seem flustered at all.

00:48:57.034 --> 00:48:58.302
Really?

00:48:58.302 --> 00:49:01.070
I do tend to adapt quickly.

00:49:01.439 --> 00:49:02.072
Anyway...

00:49:02.072 --> 00:49:03.841
- Great work.
- Great work.

00:49:03.841 --> 00:49:05.543
(They say their final goodbyes)
Great work.

00:49:05.543 --> 00:49:08.646
(KARINA leaves the set)
Bye, RINA. Great work, and thank you.

00:49:08.646 --> 00:49:11.515
You all worked so hard.

00:49:11.515 --> 00:49:13.150
It was my first time doing a shoot like this.

00:49:13.150 --> 00:49:14.552
It's not something we usually do.

00:49:14.552 --> 00:49:16.387
It was our first time too.

00:49:16.387 --> 00:49:18.389
It was everyone's first time.

00:49:18.389 --> 00:49:19.924
It was my first time, and yours too.

00:49:19.924 --> 00:49:21.125
But thanks to you, it went well.

00:49:21.125 --> 00:49:23.194
Thank you so much for your work.

00:49:23.194 --> 00:49:25.396
Do we need any pickup shots?

00:49:25.396 --> 00:49:26.230
We're good.

00:49:26.230 --> 00:49:28.499
We're good? Then can we send the actors home?

00:49:28.499 --> 00:49:29.233
You can go home.

00:49:29.233 --> 00:49:30.968
Thank you.

00:49:30.968 --> 00:49:33.838
(Today's shoot came together
through everyone's efforts)

00:49:33.838 --> 00:49:34.972
- Great work.
- Great work.

00:49:34.972 --> 00:49:37.908
(They wrap things up now)

00:49:40.344 --> 00:49:42.580
(One week later)

00:49:44.148 --> 00:49:47.251
(The two producers finished editing
with their team producers)

00:49:48.486 --> 00:49:51.755
(Edit screening)

00:49:51.755 --> 00:49:53.390
With a dramatized piece like this,

00:49:53.390 --> 00:49:55.759
this one moment of hesitation, kind of...

00:49:55.759 --> 00:50:00.130
(After feedback, each finished their clip)
I was similar to the cut before she ground it...

00:50:01.232 --> 00:50:05.135
(The two clips were uploaded)

00:50:05.536 --> 00:50:08.939
(We now reveal the results of Round 1)

00:50:09.707 --> 00:50:10.708
(July 6 (Mon))
It's not over yet.

00:50:10.708 --> 00:50:11.842
- Over.
- It's over.

00:50:13.777 --> 00:50:16.580
(Voting closed)

00:50:17.114 --> 00:50:18.549
(Tallying results)

00:50:18.549 --> 00:50:20.518
(Yoon Jun Wi/Finance team
/Math major from a prestigious U.S. university)

00:50:20.518 --> 00:50:22.320
Here are the views.

00:50:22.586 --> 00:50:25.289
(Views &lt;Alternate World&gt; 882,301
